Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.00,0:00:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}中文字幕+时间轴: EzDone Studio & MarcusZ{\r}\NSubtitle & Timeline: EzDone Studio & MarcusZ
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs48\1c&HFF00FF&}乔布斯传{\r}\N{\fs48}jOBS{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}苹果公司议事厅\N员工大会, 2001年{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.75,0:01:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我很开心来到这里.{\r}\NI'm really excited to be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.25,0:01:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天, 我们将给大家展示一个非常特殊的产品.{\r}\NWe have something really special to share with you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:30.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}在今年, iMac和Powerbook加起来,{\r}\NIn total, between iMac and PowerBook lines,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.59,0:01:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们一共卖掉300多万台.{\r}\Nwe have sold over three million units this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.39,0:01:41.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}行, 就这样了.{\r}\NOkay. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.35,0:01:45.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对了, 还有一件事.{\r}\NWell, maybe there's one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.19,0:01:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要给大家展示一件令人惊奇的产品.{\r}\NI'm about to show you something that's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.48,0:01:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一件前所未有, 闻所未闻的产品.{\r}\NSomething that no one else in the world has seen yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.28,0:01:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 强尼, 我, 还有一小组人{\r}\NNow, Jony, myself and a small team
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.16,0:02:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们非常辛苦为这个秘密的项目工作着.{\r}\Nhave been working really hard on a secret project,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.83,0:02:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家也知道我在忙这个项目,{\r}\Nwhich is something I've been known to do
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.33,0:02:06.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一直在忙于此.{\r}\Nfrom time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.38,0:02:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我马上要介绍的这款产品{\r}\NThe device I'm about to introduce to you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.63,0:02:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}将改变整个产业.{\r}\Nis gonna revolutionize an entire industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.97,0:02:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是一款音乐播放设备.{\r}\NIt's a music playing device.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.43,0:02:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们一会儿再谈细节.{\r}\NWe'll get to that in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为我想先说, 它所代表的意义和它的实际用途同样的伟大.{\r}\NBecause what it represents is as important as what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.31,0:02:29.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是一个能触动心灵的工具.{\r}\NIt's a tool for the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.90,0:02:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当某样东西能触碰一个人心灵的时候,{\r}\NAnd when you can touch someone's heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.11,0:02:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它就变得意义非凡.{\r}\Nthat's limitless.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.32,0:02:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我自卖自夸一下, 这东西酷毙了.{\r}\NIf I do say so myself, it's insanely cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.79,0:02:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是一款音乐播放器.{\r}\NIt's a music player.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.42,0:02:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}也就是在你口袋里装下一千首歌.{\r}\NIt's a thousand songs in your pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我将给你们介绍:{\r}\NI'd like to introduce you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.31,0:03:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\N...iPod\Nto the iPod.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.97,0:03:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 乔布斯.{\r}\NHey, Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.35,0:03:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}起床了, 哥们, 醒醒.{\r}\NGet up, man. Wake up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:51.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我醒着.{\r}\NI'm up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.53,0:03:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我醒着.{\r}\NI'm up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.95,0:04:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我醒着呢.{\r}\NI'm up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.05,0:04:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 嗨, 丹尼尔.  - 嘿, 忙什么呢?{\r}\N- Hey, Daniel. - Hey, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.72,0:04:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你在读那本"活在当下"的书吧?  - 是啊, 那本书很棒.{\r}\N- Are you reading Be Here Now? - Yeah, it's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我正在读, 很好看.{\r}\NI'm reading that right now. It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.89,0:04:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是一本更高层面的书. 嗯, 既然我们碰上了,{\r}\NIt's the next level. Hey, speaking of Be Here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.23,0:04:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}跟我说说昨天晚上干什么了? 你去哪儿了?{\r}\Nwhat happened to you last night? Where'd you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我得上课去了. 我知道, 我知道.{\r}\NI had to study. I know, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.81,0:04:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道的, 我不是宣讲"读书无用论",{\r}\NYou know, I'm not dismissing the value of higher education,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.07,0:04:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是上大学是以丧失实际工作经验为代价的.{\r}\NI'm just saying it comes at the expense of experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.28,0:04:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}系统化教学的产物就是系统的一部分...{\r}\NThe system can only produce the system.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我可不想变成一个死板的书呆子, 你也应该如此.{\r}\NI don't want to be a part of that. Neither should you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.49,0:04:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我同意你. 不过人要有足够胆量才能像你一样休学.{\r}\NI agree with you. It takes balls to drop out like you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.41,0:04:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是为什么你也应该休学.{\r}\NThat's why you should.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.08,0:04:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我可不行. 我是说... - 史蒂文.{\r}\N- I can't. I mean that... - Steven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.25,0:04:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}能借过跟你聊两句吗?{\r}\NMight I borrow you for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.38,0:04:54.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 打断你们了, 再见.  - 一定的.{\r}\N- I'll see you in, see you later. - Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.92,0:04:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 谢谢.  - 我希望我没有打断你们的谈兴正浓.{\r}\N- Thank you. - So I hope I'm not interrupting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:04:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你的课程上得怎么样?{\r}\NWhat about your classes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.42,0:05:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不再是学生了, 杰克.{\r}\NI'm not a student anymore, Jack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.92,0:05:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 你在这里(旁听), 学习.{\r}\NWell, you're here, and you're learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.76,0:05:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}于我而言, 你跟学生没什么分别.{\r}\NSure sounds like a student to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.85,0:05:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你想赶我走...{\r}\NIf you want me gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.43,0:05:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我为什么要赶你走啊, 史蒂夫?{\r}\NWhy would I want you gone, Steven?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.68,0:05:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我很高兴你愿意待在这里.{\r}\NI'm glad that you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.10,0:05:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}付不付学费都没关系.{\r}\NWhether you're paying or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.19,0:05:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 你经常拿个本子闲晃,{\r}\NNow, you're always carrying this notebook around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.94,0:05:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}貌似你自诩是个艺术家吧.{\r}\NYou obviously fancy yourself as an artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.48,0:05:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为什么不去上个设计类的课程呢?{\r}\NWhy don't you sit in on some design classes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不. 呃, 我喜欢艺术之美, 但是仅限于言之有物的那种艺术.{\r}\NNo. Well, I like the idea of art, the beauty. But only in the right context.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.36,0:05:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是我并不想以此为职业生涯. 我没有那种天分.{\r}\NJust not as a career. I don't have the necessary talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.49,0:05:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你不是对电子设备感兴趣吗? 工程类课程如何?{\r}\NBut aren't you interested in electronics? What about engineering?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.66,0:05:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}合格的工程师的就业前景看涨. 你看这主意怎么样?{\r}\NThere's a growing market for qualified technicians. What about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不想花我父母的钱{\r}\NI don't want to spend my parents' money
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.16,0:05:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}去读取一个学位了事, 而且不想成为...{\r}\Nto get a degree and become something
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这么容易被人淡忘的电气工程师.{\r}\Nas forgettable as an electrician.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.29,0:05:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}等会儿, 什么, 读取一个学位是虚度光阴? 因此...{\r}\NExcuse me, what, a degree is a waste of time now? So...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.42,0:05:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对某些人而言是的. 对另外一些人而言, 它是很有效的证明. 工作保证.{\r}\NFor some. For others it offers validation. Job security.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.64,0:05:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫... - 拜拜.{\r}\N- Steve... - I'll see you around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂文.{\r}\NSteven.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.45,0:05:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那下次再聊.{\r}\NTo be continued.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.94,0:06:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你在干什么?{\r}\NWhat are you working on?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没什么, 书法课的家庭作业而已.{\r}\NNothing, really. It's homework for calligraphy class.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很漂亮啊.{\r}\NIt's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.91,0:06:14.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的, 这门课的老师是一位僧侣.{\r}\NYeah, the teacher's this monk, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}僧侣?{\r}\NA monk?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 他叫罗伯特.帕拉迪诺.{\r}\NYeah. Robert Palladino.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.46,0:06:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他的课非常有启发性.{\r}\NHe's totally inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对了, 我叫茱莉.{\r}\NMy name's Julie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.02,0:06:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你要走啊?{\r}\NAre you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.35,0:06:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是啊. 我得走了.{\r}\NYeah. I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.19,0:06:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}来点吗?{\r}\NYou want a hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.86,0:06:42.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好的.{\r}\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好的, 来一点.{\r}\NYes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我能多拿点吗?{\r}\NCan I take a couple?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.78,0:06:51.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 当然.  - 给我朋友.{\r}\N- Sure. - For my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.08,0:06:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 我朋友...还有我女朋友.{\r}\NWell, my friend, and my girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好美.{\r}\NIt's so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.76,0:07:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好像一扇通往整个世界的窗户.{\r}\NLike a window to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.47,0:07:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得太空是什么样子?{\r}\NWhat do you think it's like in space?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一定...{\r}\NIt's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.35,0:07:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}美到无以言表.{\r}\Nbeyond understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.86,0:07:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.82,0:07:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁会做那种事: 生了一个孩子,{\r}\NWho has a baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}...之后, 就那样无情地抛弃掉?{\r}\Nand then just throws it away like it's nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.45,0:07:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你又在想你亲生父母的事?{\r}\NYou talking about your birth parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.71,0:07:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 别说了, 别说了.{\r}\NOh, no, no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.46,0:07:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好伤感. 真的, 太令我伤感了. 我...{\r}\NThat's bad. Yeah. That's making me really sad. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.97,0:07:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 我的过去让你High不起来了.{\r}\NSorry that my life is ruining your high.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.85,0:07:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没关系.{\r}\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.27,0:07:58.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当你不在的时候, 我会想你的.{\r}\NI miss you when you're not around.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.28,0:08:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我爱你, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NI love you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.24,0:08:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我爱你.{\r}\NI love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.37,0:08:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}宇宙啊, 无边无垠的黑暗王国.{\r}\NSpace. The endless black deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}到底过去的哲人告诉了我们什么?{\r}\NWhat was it that that guru used to tell us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.55,0:08:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别蹉跎岁月.{\r}\NThere is no time to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.01,0:08:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你听见了吗?{\r}\NDo you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.72,0:08:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么?{\r}\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.16,0:08:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他又去了远方.{\r}\NThere he goes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.14,0:09:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}书法是一种把艺术和视觉结合的表现形式.{\r}\NCalligraphy is the artful and visual expression of communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比如说Garamond字体{\r}\NTake Garamond, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.73,0:09:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}特殊的字体设计是为了让每一种阅读体验{\r}\NA typeface specifically designed to make the very act of reading
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.27,0:09:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}更加的自然.{\r}\Nmore natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}电脑之所以被发明, 是为了让人们的生活更容易.{\r}\NComputers are inherently designed to make your lives easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.96,0:09:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}理论上讲, 没有什么是电脑做不到的.{\r}\NTheoretically there's no limit to what computers can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.64,0:10:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你出生时是谁, 并不重要；{\r}\NIt is not who you were at birth that matters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.69,0:10:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}重要的是, 你在有生之年做了什么.{\r}\Nbut what you do with the time you are given.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.11,0:10:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}人生苦短,{\r}\NThe moment of your death is fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.78,0:10:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}在生命的终点, 一切将归于平静.{\r}\NLife is but a journey to serenity, to its completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.09,0:10:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}简单地做好自己.{\r}\NBe as simple as you can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.63,0:10:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你会惊奇地发现生活变得简单{\r}\NYou'll be astonished to see how uncomplicated
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.84,0:10:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且快乐.{\r}\Nand happy your life can become.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.86,0:11:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不知道我回家了要做什么.{\r}\NI don't even know what I'm gonna do when I go back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.54,0:11:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你呢?{\r}\NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}回到矽谷后你想做什么?{\r}\NWhat are you gonna do when you get back to The Valley?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.25,0:11:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫?{\r}\NSteve?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.46,0:11:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫? 你还好吗?{\r}\NSteve? You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.93,0:11:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不, 不! 这还是黑白两色的.{\r}\NNo. No, no! No. It's still black and white.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.65,0:11:30.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}老百姓想要彩色的.{\r}\NPeople want color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.31,0:11:32.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 这产品过去一直没有彩色的.  - 那么?{\r}\N- Pong didn't have color. - So?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}让我们把产品做得更好一点点.{\r}\NLet's do something better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这东西没办法做成彩色的.{\r}\NIt can't do color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.74,0:11:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁说的?{\r}\NSays who?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.07,0:11:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好. 你不愿意做任何努力.{\r}\NOkay, you refuse to do anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.28,0:11:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}稍微困难一点的事情你就放弃.{\r}\Nthat vaguely escapes your comfort zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.41,0:11:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你又不是我老板.{\r}\NYou're not even my boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 我觉得我应该做你的老板.{\r}\NWell, I damn sure should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.95,0:11:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 乔布斯!{\r}\NHey. Jobs!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你在干嘛呢, 史蒂夫?{\r}\NWhat're you doing, Steve?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.21,0:11:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他就是个蠢货.{\r}\NHe's an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.50,0:11:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们知道的, 这屋子里一半的人{\r}\NYou know, and half the people around here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}根本不懂设计产品.{\r}\Ndon't know how to design shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家对你的行为很不满.{\r}\NPeople are complaining about your behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.42,0:12:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 怎么啦? 没错. - 有关我的?{\r}\N- Okay? And, yeah. - About mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.18,0:12:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还有你身上的味道.{\r}\NAnd your odor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要你去洗澡, 你洗了吗?{\r}\NAre you showering like we discussed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.85,0:12:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你要我不要打赤脚, 我已经照做了.{\r}\NI'm wearing shoes. You asked me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.02,0:12:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我确实穿上鞋子了.{\r}\Nto wear shoes, and I've got them on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这不是问题的关键所在, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NThat's not part of the deal, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.81,0:12:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你得学会跟别人共事.{\r}\NYou've gotta learn how to work well with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.69,0:12:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我只是想把事情做得好一些.{\r}\NI'm just trying to do it right, Al.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.32,0:12:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道.{\r}\NI know you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那就别管我.{\r}\NThen let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.78,0:12:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 史蒂夫!{\r}\NListen, Steve!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.95,0:12:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你很棒, 非常棒!{\r}\NYou're good. You're damn good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.62,0:12:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你就是个浑球.{\r}\NBut you're an asshole.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.41,0:12:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 天哪...{\r}\NWell, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.54,0:12:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 让我说完.{\r}\NHey. Let me finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.79,0:12:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想让你待在这里, 我真心这样想.{\r}\NI want you here. I really do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.00,0:12:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你必须改变自己.{\r}\NSomething's gotta change.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.51,0:12:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 让我独自做一个项目.  - 什么?{\r}\N- Give me my own project. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}把我自己的项目交给我做.{\r}\NGive me my own project.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.59,0:12:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我独自一人完成.{\r}\NI'll do it on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.43,0:12:48.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我会做一个你从没见过的好游戏.{\r}\NAnd I'll make the best damn game you have ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.43,0:12:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你说真的.{\r}\NYou're serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.15,0:12:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NOkay, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.27,0:12:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我需要有人重新制作一些有问题的游戏.{\r}\NI need someone to reprogram a troublesome game.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.03,0:12:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是我时间上很紧张.{\r}\NBut I'm on a tight deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你能如期完工,{\r}\NSo if you can deliver,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.15,0:13:02.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我会付给你5,000美元.{\r}\Nwe'll pay you up to $5,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 5,000美元?  - 呣...{\r}\N- $5,000? - Mmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好的.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.29,0:13:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}至于你的个人问题, 我有办法能解决.{\r}\NAnd as for your personal issues, I think I may have a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.01,0:13:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这有很多电路板.{\r}\NIt's so many circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}沃兹? 嘿, 我是史蒂夫.{\r}\NWoz? Hey, it's Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.75,0:14:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你帮忙.{\r}\NThanks for saving my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.88,0:14:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没事, 我们是朋友. 这正是好朋友应该做的.{\r}\NOf course. We're friends. That's, that's what friends do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.56,0:14:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我实在没办法给别人打工.{\r}\NI just can't work for other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我需要独立行动, 如果这事儿合理的话.{\r}\NI guess I need my independence. If that makes any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.62,0:14:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃-哈.{\r}\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.33,0:14:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得非常合理.{\r}\NThat makes perfect sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.17,0:14:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 大好的周末夜被我毁了.{\r}\NI'm sorry for ruining your Friday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.09,0:14:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你在开玩笑吧? 这事儿很棒.{\r}\NAre you kidding me? This is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我喜欢免费做这件事, 真的.{\r}\NI'd do this for free. I really would.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是, 好奇的是, 这个项目我们能拿多少钱?{\r}\NBut just out of curiosity, how much are we getting paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.01,0:14:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}700美元.{\r}\N$700.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.56,0:14:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好多啊.{\r}\NSome big bucks there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.66,0:15:09.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}靠.{\r}\NShit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}真不错. 非常好.{\r}\NThis is good. Really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道.{\r}\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.33,0:15:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喔, 4天就搞定, 你真不是盖的.{\r}\NWow. Four days. You aren't kidding around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我还得给诺兰看一眼, 不过这真的很不错.{\r}\NI'll have to show it to Nolan, but this is, this is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.94,0:15:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}沃兹?{\r}\NWoz?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.06,0:15:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨. 嗨.{\r}\NHi. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}沃兹!{\r}\NWoz!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.23,0:15:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨! 是的, 我在客厅里.{\r}\NHi! Yeah, I'm in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.74,0:15:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿. 好消息.{\r}\NHey. Good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.57,0:15:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃? 我猜你老板喜欢那个游戏.{\r}\NHuh? Let me guess, your bosses liked the video game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.07,0:15:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 他们确实喜欢!  - 哦.{\r}\N- They loved it! - Ooh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.04,0:15:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}350美元! 唉哟, 不错的买卖哦.{\r}\N$350. Whew! That's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.37,0:15:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不只是不错, 简直是超屌.{\r}\NNot bad? It's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.58,0:16:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你在忙什么呢?{\r}\NWhat are you working on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:03.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我在给"对话式笑话机器"写笑话.{\r}\NI'm writing jokes for my dial-a-joke machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.59,0:16:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我写出了不少绝对好笑的波兰笑话, 因为我是波兰人.{\r}\NI've got some really good funny Polish jokes, which work because I'm Polish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.05,0:16:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}出去走走, 听听这段, 你觉得怎么样?{\r}\NHang out and tell me what you think of this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.93,0:16:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}准备好了吗?{\r}\NReady? Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.09,0:16:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}新婚之夜, 波兰新娘会得到什么"长而硬"的东东?{\r}\NWhat is long, and hard, that a Polish bride gets on her wedding night?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.93,0:16:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一个新的姓氏(从夫姓).{\r}\NA new last name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.77,0:16:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}蛮好笑的.{\r}\NThat's hilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.94,0:16:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不错吧, 对不对?{\r}\NPretty good, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.86,0:16:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你遇见一个漂亮的波兰女孩, 你会叫她什么? 幸运妹.{\r}\NWhat do you call a beautiful Polish girl? Lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.86,0:16:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那是什么?{\r}\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呣?{\r}\NHmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.08,0:16:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦.{\r}\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个可厉害了.{\r}\NThat. Now that is gonna be cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.62,0:16:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是个我正在研发的"个人电脑终端主板".{\r}\NIt's a computer terminal board I'm working on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.38,0:16:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}可以直接连上电视.{\r}\NHooks up to the TV for the display.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.09,0:16:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}看起来像什么, 一个盒子? 你什么意思啊?{\r}\NWhat is it like, a kit? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.72,0:16:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 呃...{\r}\NWell, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.80,0:16:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}代码还有些毛病.{\r}\NThe code is still buggy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.05,0:16:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}理论上, 这能在荧幕上即时显示你的操作. 例如...{\r}\Nbut in theory it'll display whatever you're working on. Like...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.35,0:16:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}弄来看看.{\r}\NShow me.
