Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.48,0:22:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}打扰一下. 我叫保罗.特里尔.{\r}\NExcuse me. Name is Paul Terrell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.07,0:22:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我看了你们的展示.{\r}\NI saw your presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.94,0:22:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎样?{\r}\NAnd?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.07,0:22:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想谈谈生意.{\r}\NAnd I'd like to talk business.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.36,0:22:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 怎么谈?  - 好...{\r}\N- What can I do for you? - Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.32,0:22:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我在Mountainview市有家电脑配件店.{\r}\NI own a local computer parts store, in Mountainview.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.66,0:22:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}店名叫位元电脑商店?{\r}\NThe Byte Shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.87,0:22:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你购买电脑配件.{\r}\NYou buy computer parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.16,0:22:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的, 我销售各类电子器件, 晶体管, 电焊设备, 屏幕之类的.{\r}\NYeah. We sell transistors, boards, soldering equipment, monitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.71,0:22:59.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道的, 兴趣使然的那种.{\r}\NYou know, hobbyist types.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.25,0:23:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}像"灿坤"电气连锁店那样?{\r}\NLike Radio Shack?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.00,0:23:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不.{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.34,0:23:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 你来我店里看看就知道了.{\r}\NListen, why don't you stop by and talk to me some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.22,0:23:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是我名片, 记得给我打电话.{\r}\NThere's my card. Give me a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.05,0:23:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很好.{\r}\NGreat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.18,0:23:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很高兴见到你.{\r}\NIt was nice meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.97,0:23:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我叫史蒂夫.乔布斯.{\r}\NSteve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.18,0:23:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.乔布斯. 好!{\r}\NSteve Jobs. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.77,0:23:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那个人谁是啊?{\r}\NWho was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.61,0:23:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 那是保罗.特里尔 - 哦.{\r}\N- It's Paul Terrell. - Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.74,0:23:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁?{\r}\NWho?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.44,0:24:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想要投资多少钱?{\r}\NSo what kind of investment are we talking about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.73,0:24:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}天啊, 史蒂夫. 我只是说我有兴趣, 没说我想买.{\r}\NJesus, Steve. I said I was interested, not buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.61,0:24:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道, 但你不是唯一的对我们感兴趣的意向买家.{\r}\NI know. But you're also not the only interested party.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.16,0:24:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 啊, 不是吧? 我不是唯一的?  - 不是的.{\r}\N- Oh, really? I'm not? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.95,0:24:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你不是.  - 呣.{\r}\N- You're not. - Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.08,0:24:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有点意思.{\r}\NThat's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.25,0:24:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那天晚上在Homebrew会场上的情况看起来可不乐观啊.{\r}\NBecause it sure seemed that way the other night at Homebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.46,0:24:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你以为那是我们去的第一个会场吗?{\r}\NYou think that's the first stop that we made?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.88,0:24:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}全硅谷我们都去过了.{\r}\NWe've been all over The Valley.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.38,0:24:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 呃, 你已经找到了零售商.{\r}\NOh, well, then you already have a retailer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有那么几个报价.{\r}\NI got offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.01,0:24:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}...听我说, 保罗. 我全名里面也有保罗(史蒂夫.保罗.乔布斯). 我爸也是.{\r}\NLook, Paul. My middle name's Paul. My dad's name is Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.47,0:24:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一群人叫保罗, 我...{\r}\NBunch of Pauls. I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.30,0:24:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我认为, 我们有共同点.{\r}\NI think we're kindred spirits here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.60,0:24:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们都是有着非凡直觉的商人.{\r}\NWe're both businessmen that operate from our gut.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.06,0:24:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}直觉告诉我, 你应该抓住机会跟我们做生意.{\r}\NAnd my gut tells me to give you this opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.07,0:24:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我考虑400美元一台, 要50台, 货到付款.{\r}\NI'm thinking $400 per machine, for 50 units, paid at the time of delivery.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.78,0:24:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}400美元一台, 定货100台, 预付三分之一的款.{\r}\N$400 for a hundred units, a third up front.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.87,0:24:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不想讨价还价.{\r}\NWe're not negotiating.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:24:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 我想.{\r}\NYes, we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.91,0:25:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 我付450美元一台, 450美元.{\r}\NOkay. I'll pay $450 per machine. $450.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.34,0:25:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}货到付款, 不预付. 我知道很有挑战, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NOn delivery, nothing up front. I know it's asking a lot, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.30,0:25:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这可是一大笔钱, 如果你能按时交货.{\r}\NBut it's a big payoff if you deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.30,0:25:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我交货的时候...{\r}\NWhen I deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.64,0:25:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}500美元一台就成交.{\r}\N$500 per unit and you've got a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.65,0:25:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 三个月内交货.{\r}\NAll right. You got 90 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.99,0:25:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}两个月就够了.{\r}\NI'll have it in 60.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.08,0:25:39.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}丹尼尔和我没有地方了, 因此...{\r}\NDaniel and I just didn't have room at our place, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.95,0:25:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不. 我很高兴你能求我帮忙.{\r}\NNo, no. I'm glad you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.44,0:25:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}既然我们能帮忙...{\r}\NNow we could...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.67,0:25:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}把东西搬走, 再清理打扫一下.{\r}\Nmove some things around, give it a good cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.50,0:25:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我会把我的工具搬到工具房里去.{\r}\NI could move most of my tools to the shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.84,0:25:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}热的时候再给你们弄台电风扇.{\r}\NMaybe get you boys a fan when it gets hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.72,0:25:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦.{\r}\NOoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.30,0:25:56.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么样?{\r}\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.51,0:25:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}太完美了, 老爸.{\r}\NIt's great, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.93,0:26:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的. 这太棒了.{\r}\NYes. It is. This is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.56,0:26:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那就好, 希望你们能做点大事.{\r}\NGood. Well, it'll be good to see you building something.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.02,0:26:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好了. 嘿, 保持整洁.{\r}\NGood. Hey, keep it neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.86,0:26:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}里里外外都要整洁.{\r}\NInside and out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.40,0:26:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 谢谢, 杰克先生.  - 呣.{\r}\N- Thanks, Mr. J. - Mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.91,0:26:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们有自己的店面了.{\r}\NWe got a shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.79,0:26:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的.{\r}\NYes, we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.22,0:26:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么样?{\r}\NHow's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.60,0:26:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}搞定.{\r}\NVoila.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.69,0:26:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这应该直一点, 那个应该对称.{\r}\NIt's gotta be straighter. These have to be more symmetrical.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.36,0:26:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们在两个月内要做50个主机板,{\r}\NWe have 60 days to complete 50 of these,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.11,0:26:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你还在意什么对称不对称吗?{\r}\Nand you're worried about the symmetry?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.62,0:27:01.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 没有人会在意主板的样子.{\r}\NSteve, nobody cares about the look of the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.12,0:27:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我在意.  - 好吧, 挺不错.{\r}\N- I care. - Well, that's just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.33,0:27:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你夸口两个月就交货的时候, 我们就制定时间不多了.{\r}\NBut we were out of time the minute you made that stupid promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.79,0:27:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你说得对.{\r}\NYou're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.50,0:27:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们需要人帮忙.{\r}\NNeed help.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.17,0:27:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 沃兹... - 干嘛?{\r}\N- Woz. - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.38,0:27:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我们有麻烦了.  - 呃?{\r}\N- We got a problem. - Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.47,0:27:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们得想办法怎样安排这几个员工.{\r}\NWe got to figure out what to do with all these employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.22,0:27:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你认识比尔? - 比尔.{\r}\N- You know Bill? - Bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.35,0:27:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 好久不见, 沃兹.  - 最近怎样?{\r}\N- Too long, Woz. - How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.10,0:27:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很高兴见到你. 大家伙怎样?{\r}\NGood to see you. How is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.44,0:27:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 这位是我的朋友丹尼尔.阔特科.{\r}\NOh, this is my friend Daniel Kottke.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.65,0:27:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你好, 久仰大名. 最近怎样?{\r}\NHey. I've heard a lot about you. How're you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.40,0:27:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}克特科? 就是你和老乔一起去印度的, 当然知道你的大名.{\r}\NKottke? Kottke from India, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.82,0:27:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对你, 我也是久仰大名.{\r}\NI've heard a lot about you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.28,0:27:37.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别碰.{\r}\NDon't touch that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.24,0:27:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是克里斯, 就是我说过的邻居小孩?{\r}\NThat's Chris Espinosa. Kid down the street I was telling you about?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.99,0:27:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 很高兴来这里, 伙计们.  - 太酷了.{\r}\N- Nice to meet you, fella. - This is gonna be so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.74,0:27:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不错, 很高兴你喜欢这里.{\r}\NGreat. I'm so glad that you're excited
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.04,0:27:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喜欢我们正在做的事情.{\r}\Nabout this thing we're doing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.71,0:27:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}能私下聊两句吗?{\r}\NCan I talk to you for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.92,0:27:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}可以.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.04,0:27:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对不起, 别动, 站一边去.{\r}\NExcuse me, just please stop. And go over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.80,0:27:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别碍事, 都站一边去.{\r}\NJust out of the way, over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.18,0:28:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们目前请不起三个人.{\r}\NWe can't afford to pay three people right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.10,0:28:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们自己都开不出工资, 除非我们按时交货.{\r}\NWe can't afford to pay ourselves, unless we deliver.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.19,0:28:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别管克里斯, 他就是一小屁孩, 他就是想(免费)帮忙.{\r}\NAnd don't worry about Chris. He's just a kid. So he just wants to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.78,0:28:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你才是小屁孩.{\r}\NYou're just a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.78,0:28:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}笑一下...{\r}\NCheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.62,0:28:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢了, 妈妈.{\r}\NThanks, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.87,0:28:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}太冏了.{\r}\NSo embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.70,0:29:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 好了. - 说到做到.{\r}\N- All right. - As promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.16,0:29:53.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这主机板不错.{\r}\NNice board.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.63,0:30:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}其余的部分在哪儿?{\r}\NWhere's the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.92,0:30:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}其余的? 就这些了.{\r}\NThe rest? This is all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.64,0:30:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要的是50台电脑.{\r}\NI asked for 50 computers.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.26,0:30:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}包括键盘, 机壳, 屏幕, 电源等全部的东西.{\r}\NThat's keyboards, cases, monitors, and power included.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.10,0:30:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不是光秃秃的主机板.{\r}\NNot just boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.31,0:30:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么叫光秃秃的主机板? 这可是最新科技.{\r}\NJust boards? Excuse me? Just boards? These are state-of-the-art.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.69,0:30:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们的逻辑电路板是...没有人做得出来.{\r}\NThe logic boards alone are... Nobody's making anything like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.07,0:30:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们是. 你怎么能这么说话?{\r}\NThey're, what, how dare you! How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.82,0:30:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我同事是想说...{\r}\NI think what my colleague is saying is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.53,0:30:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你没看到这蕴藏的大好机会.{\r}\NYou're not seeing the possibilities here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.91,0:30:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这实际上是一台令人难以置信的"强悍"的电脑.{\r}\NThat is indeed one unbelievably kick ass computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.12,0:30:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对顾客来说可不是.{\r}\NNot to the consumer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.17,0:30:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 所以可能你的顾客{\r}\NWell, then maybe your consumer
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.54,0:30:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}应该学学怎么用...{\r}\Nshould start to learn how to...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.17,0:30:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么使用这种电脑, 不是吗?{\r}\NHow to even work that, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.68,0:30:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 兄弟.{\r}\NListen, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.42,0:30:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们卖给我的应该是一台完整电脑.  有键盘和荧幕的那种.{\r}\NYou sold me on a home computer. That's a keyboard and monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.14,0:30:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就一个主机板, 没了.{\r}\NThis is a board.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.18,0:30:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 这是个不错的基础{\r}\NNow, I'm sure this makes a very capable starter kit,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.14,0:30:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但对于一般用户,{\r}\Nbut the everyday person,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.64,0:30:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不是工程师的那种人,{\r}\Nthe kind of person that's not an engineer,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.77,0:30:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}也不是向你一样的电脑俱乐部出身,{\r}\Nor in a computer club like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.02,0:31:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}根本搞不懂这东西怎么用.{\r}\Nthey're not gonna know what the hell this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.48,0:31:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一般用户根本不想学自己组装一台电脑.{\r}\NThe average Joe doesn't want to build their own computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.69,0:31:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们只想买回去,{\r}\NThey just want to buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.11,0:31:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}拆开盒子, 插上电源,{\r}\NThey want to take it out of the box, plug it in,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.53,0:31:09.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就能用了.{\r}\Nand have it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.57,0:31:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得呢, 史蒂夫?{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.87,0:31:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你有在听吗?{\r}\NAre you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.25,0:31:18.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的, 这是你的主机板.{\r}\NYeah. These are your boards.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.67,0:31:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你一定能卖出去.{\r}\NAnd they will sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.46,0:31:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我保证这点.{\r}\NI can promise you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.84,0:31:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你不是看了我们在Homebrew的展示吗!{\r}\NYou saw our demo at Homebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.72,0:31:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道加上一些外围设备, 这东西就能有多强悍.{\r}\NYou know what it's capable of with the right components,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.84,0:31:32.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且, 这些外围设备, 你这里都有卖.{\r}\Nwhich, by the way, all of which you sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.39,0:31:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}给客户展示一下.{\r}\NSo, demo it to the consumer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.60,0:31:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且外围设备可以单独卖钱.{\r}\NAnd market the components separately.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.85,0:31:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你展示一下你店里的键盘, 荧幕.{\r}\NYou show them your keyboards, and your monitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.11,0:31:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}客户会在店里买这些配件, 你赚的更多,{\r}\NYou'll move more inventory that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.82,0:31:44.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你会赚到很多很多的现金美钞.{\r}\Nand you'll make a hell of a lot more cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.86,0:31:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}其实你赚到了.{\r}\NYou got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.16,0:31:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NAll right, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.33,0:31:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我会试试出售.{\r}\NI'll try to sell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.54,0:32:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果卖不出去, 我就不会再下单了.{\r}\NBut if I don't, I'm not making another order.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.38,0:32:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 没问题.{\r}\NOkay. That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.55,0:32:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是你肯定会对我们的第二代机型有兴趣.{\r}\NBut I think that you might be really interested in our second model.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.13,0:32:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}二代机型是什么?{\r}\NWhat's the second model?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.09,0:32:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你说什么?{\r}\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.64,0:32:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一体成型机.{\r}\NAll-in-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.17,0:32:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有什么事?{\r}\NCan I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.76,0:32:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是罗德.霍尔特.{\r}\NYeah, I'm Rod Holt.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.72,0:32:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}工程技师. 我们电话里谈过.{\r}\NThe technician. We talked on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.68,0:32:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当然. 你是罗德.{\r}\NOf course. It's Rod.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.94,0:33:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你过来一趟.{\r}\NGlad you could stop by.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.19,0:33:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}欢迎来到Apple电脑公司.{\r}\NWelcome to Apple Computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.69,0:33:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧.{\r}\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.41,0:33:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}带我看看所谓的革命性的"东东".{\r}\NShow me this revolutionary piece of shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.99,0:33:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple II 电脑.{\r}\NThe Apple ll.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.83,0:33:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是世界上第一台一体机.{\r}\NIt's the first ever all-in-one personal home computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.13,0:33:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你叫我来干什么?{\r}\NAnd you called me because?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.80,0:33:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们需要你设计一个高效率的电源. 机箱里面用的.{\r}\NWe need a heat efficient power supply. In the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.30,0:33:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得根本不可能, 但是我不介意(试试).{\r}\NThat's impossible, but don't mind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.72,0:33:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}毕竟, 我也是个工程师.{\r}\NI'm just, you know, an engineer.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.26,0:33:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}需要多大电压?{\r}\NSo, wattage?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.47,0:33:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}40瓦, 而且必须安静.{\r}\N40 watts. And quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.60,0:33:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 怎样算是"安静"?  - 最好是静音的.{\r}\N- What the hell do you mean, quiet? - I mean silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.77,0:33:44.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}目前还没有这种东东.{\r}\NThere's no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.98,0:33:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它会发热, 必须有个风扇.{\r}\NThese things run hot. They need fans in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.48,0:33:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}风扇噪音可不会小.{\r}\NThose bitches ain't quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.07,0:33:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是为什么我们需要要你来...{\r}\NThat's exactly why we need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.91,0:33:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}重新设计.{\r}\NTo redesign it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.99,0:33:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 重新设计什么?{\r}\NRedesign what?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.28,0:33:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}整个电源系统. 重新开始设计.{\r}\NThe power supply. From scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.12,0:34:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不能有风扇, 还要保证散热.{\r}\NIt can't have a fan, it can't overheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.00,0:34:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还要能装进机壳, 就这么大的机壳.{\r}\NAnd it needs to fit inside a box, this size.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.35,0:34:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别抽烟, 好吗!{\r}\NDon't do that. Please, don't do...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.18,0:34:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不管怎样, 尽你可能做吧.{\r}\NWhatever. Do whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.20,0:34:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我薪水是200美元一天.{\r}\NMy rate is $200 a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.45,0:34:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且我觉得不爽就闪人.{\r}\NAnd if I ever think things aren't working out, I walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.03,0:34:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呣-呣.{\r}\NMmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.37,0:34:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你清楚吗?{\r}\NAre we clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.70,0:34:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}明白.{\r}\NWe're clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.54,0:34:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们是在说朝阳产业.{\r}\NWe're talking about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.42,0:34:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这市场还没人开始做.{\r}\NWe're working in a market that doesn't even exist yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.71,0:34:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Intel在处理器行业做的很大,{\r}\NWhat Intel has done for the microprocessor,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.05,0:34:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们将在个人电脑领域做同样的事情.{\r}\Nwe are gonna do for the home computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.60,0:35:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么听不懂呢?{\r}\NHow can you not know what I'm talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.35,0:35:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 夫人, 它能在荧幕上显示东西.{\r}\NNo, ma'am. But it runs on a TV monitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.07,0:35:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 没错, 就像电视机.{\r}\NYes, like a television set. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.45,0:35:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我认为你可能没明白我的意思, 它不是电视.{\r}\NI don't think you understand. It's not a TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.20,0:35:19.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是个人电脑.{\r}\NIt's a personal computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.37,0:35:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 你有打字机吗{\r}\NOkay, do you own a typewriter?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.24,0:35:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 你平时会用吗? 很好.{\r}\NGreat. Okay, now do you use it? Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.08,0:35:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}想像你有一台接上电视的打字机.{\r}\NSo imagine combining your typewriter with your television set.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.21,0:35:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}等等, 等等.{\r}\NNo. Don't... Wait. Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.26,0:35:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}等等. 先生, 别挂. 请别挂断电话.{\r}\NWait. Please, sir, don't, don't hang up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.89,0:35:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 没错, 我们现在规模很小, 但是我们...{\r}\NYes. We are small right now, but we...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.27,0:35:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么知道我们在车库里工作?{\r}\NHow do you know we're working out of our garage?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.44,0:35:51.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁告诉你的?{\r}\NWho told you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.69,0:35:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊!{\r}\NAhhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.07,0:35:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 是.{\r}\NYes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.11,0:36:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你肯花时间听我说.{\r}\NWell, thank you for taking the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.12,0:36:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的, 先生, Apple电脑公司.{\r}\NYes, sir. Apple Computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.79,0:36:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple...水果那个Apple.{\r}\NApple? Yes, like the fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.30,0:36:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那是谁?{\r}\NWho's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.47,0:36:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不. 我只是想让你过来看一眼.{\r}\NNo. No. All I'm asking is that you come visit us.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.55,0:36:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就看一眼, 你绝对会感兴趣.{\r}\NOne meeting and I promise you'll be on board.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.68,0:36:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得大概5万美元.{\r}\NAround $50,000 would be my guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.60,0:36:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喂?{\r}\NHello?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.49,0:36:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们说什么?{\r}\NWhat did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.47,0:37:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这些人到底怎么回事?{\r}\NWhat the hell is the matter with people?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.22,0:37:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}看来电话打得不顺利.{\r}\NTake it the call went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.81,0:37:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我本来想说噎死你, 但是反正这种垃圾食物早晚会害死你.{\r}\NI would say I hope you choke, but that burrito is gonna kill you either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.35,0:37:14.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}放轻松, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NOh, come on, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.90,0:37:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}再说一遍, 伙计.{\r}\NCool your jets, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.23,0:37:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你太紧张了, 放松一下.{\r}\NExcuse you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.82,0:37:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}只是, 你知道的, 你太紧张了.{\r}\NJust, you know, you're so stressed, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.07,0:37:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就像为了改变而放松下来.{\r}\NIt's, like, relax for a change.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.41,0:37:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为了改变...为什么? 为了跟你俩个混蛋一样.{\r}\NFor a change... Why? Why? So I can be more like you two assholes?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.62,0:37:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 我正在学习"嵌入式电路".{\r}\NHey. I'm studying integrated circuit design here, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.21,0:37:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是吗?{\r}\NAre you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.83,0:37:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们都在做各自该做的事.{\r}\NWe each do our part.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.08,0:37:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是吗? 我怎么觉得你做的事都是没用的?{\r}\NReally? Then why do I suddenly feel like your part is expendable?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.05,0:37:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别像在印度的时候那样抽烟了. 醒醒吧, 我们不在印度了.{\r}\NOut here smokin' up like we're in India. Well, wake up! We're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.68,0:37:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么了?{\r}\NWhat happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.01,0:37:48.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你曾经很有活力的... - 什么? 我曾经怎么啦?{\r}\N- You used to be... - What? I used to be what?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.60,0:37:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 自我激励.  - 我就是自我激励.{\r}\N- Motivated. - I am motivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.27,0:37:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是吗? 表现给我看啊.{\r}\NReally? Then show me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.06,0:37:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是生意! 丹尼尔, 振作点.{\r}\NThis is a business, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.27,0:37:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你要是自己不努力, 我也束手无策.{\r}\NAnd I can't help you if you don't help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.61,0:38:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我每天打100个电话.{\r}\NI'm in there making a hundred phone calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.32,0:38:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}罗德.霍尔特在做苦力.{\r}\NRod is slaving away.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.24,0:38:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那小鬼也总能找到事情做,{\r}\NThe kid always finds something to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.16,0:38:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}沃兹每天也超努力的.{\r}\Nand God knows Woz pulls his weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.49,0:38:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢夸奖.{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.62,0:38:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}每天超努力地增肥.{\r}\NAnd that's a whole lot of weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.16,0:38:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}真是的...人家心里很受伤的.{\r}\NThat really... That kind of hurts my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.92,0:38:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦.{\r}\NWhoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.14,0:38:29.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我没走错吧...{\r}\NIs this the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.72,0:38:31.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是Apple电脑公司?{\r}\NApple Computer?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.81,0:38:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 是, 正是我们.  - 没错.{\r}\N- Yeah, this is us. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.48,0:38:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你以为会看到别的景象?{\r}\NYou expecting something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.73,0:38:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没, 嗯, 也许没想到有这么多宅男.{\r}\NUh, no. Well, yeah, maybe something a little less Manson Family.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.36,0:38:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我们还在创业的起步阶段. - 是的.{\r}\N- It's a startup. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.03,0:38:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我叫麦克.马库拉.{\r}\NI'm Mike Markkula.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.49,0:38:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是史蒂夫.乔布斯.{\r}\NSteve. Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.24,0:38:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 久仰大名.{\r}\NSteve. I heard a lot about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.41,0:38:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}董.瓦伦泰恩在电话里提过你.{\r}\NYou spoke to Don Valentine on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.91,0:38:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们是老同事.{\r}\NHe and I are old colleagues of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.08,0:38:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Atari的投资人.{\r}\NThe VC from Atari.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.00,0:39:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的, 瓦伦泰恩. 他说你打了150多通电话给他.{\r}\NYeah, Valentine. He said you called him 150 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.88,0:39:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我靠, 服了你了.{\r}\NJesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.30,0:39:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他差点跪下来求我, 要我过来看一眼.{\r}\NHe practically begged me to come and look at your outfit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.30,0:39:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我就当帮他个忙吧.{\r}\NCalled in a personal favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.85,0:39:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那好, 马克.{\r}\NWell, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.72,0:39:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.89,0:39:11.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.18,0:39:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}欢迎来到Apple电脑公司.{\r}\NWelcome to Apple Computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.35,0:39:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢了. 是的, 这是? ...{\r}\NThank you. Yeah, is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.48,0:39:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是你所有的家当?{\r}\NThis is everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.56,0:39:20.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 是的.  - 才怪.{\r}\N- Yes. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.90,0:39:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不. 我们在更好的位置还有6家零售店.{\r}\NNo. We're, we're in six stores in the greater area.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.78,0:39:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们大约一个月内会发布Apple II 电脑.{\r}\NWe'll be launching the Apple ll in about a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.40,0:39:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 还有好几个月.  - 很接近.{\r}\N- In a few months. - It's close.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.49,0:39:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}各位, 有地方能坐下来好好谈谈吗?{\r}\NGentlemen, is there some place we can talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.66,0:39:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是你的.{\r}\NHere you are, fellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.58,0:39:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是你的.{\r}\NFor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.92,0:39:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫是素食主义者, 狂吃水果.{\r}\NSteve's a fruitarian. He will only eat fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.47,0:39:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好啦, 你们谈生意吧.{\r}\NOkay, boys. I'll just... I'll leave you to your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.51,0:39:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢.{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.68,0:39:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 谢谢啦, 妈.  - 谢谢夫人.{\r}\N- Thanks, Mom. - Thanks, Mrs. J.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.39,0:39:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你是最棒的.{\r}\NYou're the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.72,0:39:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 我们说到哪了?{\r}\NYeah. So where were we?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.14,0:40:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 不要南辕北辙了, 你从哪冒出来的?{\r}\NI'm sorry, don't take this the wrong way, but what's your angle?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.10,0:40:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃...{\r}\NUh...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.23,0:40:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我同事想问的是...{\r}\NWhat my colleague is trying to say is...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.86,0:40:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你之前在哪里工作?{\r}\NWhere was your last employment?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.03,0:40:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}英特尔.{\r}\NIntel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.20,0:40:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想投资多少?{\r}\NSo how much are we talking about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.79,0:40:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 什么, 投资?  - 你不就是为了这个来的.{\r}\N- What, the investment? - That's what you came here for.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.70,0:40:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫不会说客套话.{\r}\NForeplay is not Steve's strong suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.92,0:40:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我没说错吧?{\r}\NIsn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.21,0:40:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 嗯,{\r}\NYeah, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.42,0:40:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我在找一个真正值得投资的东西.{\r}\NI've been looking for something to really sink my teeth into.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.43,0:40:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 史蒂夫. 我愿意冒险.{\r}\NLook, Steve. I'm willing to take the risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.64,0:40:42.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个公司看起来值得冒险.{\r}\NAnd, this certainly qualifies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.36,0:40:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是要能保证我不会平白承担风险.{\r}\NBut risk disguised as promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.40,0:40:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道你是个有担当的. 我看得出来.{\r}\NAnd you've shown promise. I've seen it in your eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.73,0:40:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我看得出来, 因为我跟你一样.{\r}\Nand I know that look because I've had it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.24,0:40:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}直觉告诉我, 你会有大作为.{\r}\NTells me you're on to something big.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.08,0:41:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 说正经的.{\r}\NYeah. Okay. To the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.08,0:41:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想先投资9万美元.{\r}\NI think we should start with around 90 grand,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.00,0:41:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}看看这笔投资的结果如何.{\r}\Nsee where that takes us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.59,0:41:10.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}行, 对不起. 你能再说一遍吗?{\r}\NOkay, I'm sorry. Could you repeat that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.63,0:41:11.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思.{\r}\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.59,0:41:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}9万美元可能不够.{\r}\N$90,000 isn't gonna get it done.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.47,0:41:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 史蒂夫, 等等.{\r}\NOh, whoa, whoa. Wait. Steve, one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.76,0:41:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还有别人会跑到一个车库里投资吗?{\r}\NI don't see anybody else coming in your garage with a checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.10,0:41:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不是这意思.{\r}\NOh, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.35,0:41:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}9万美元对我们是够了.{\r}\NNinety grand gets it done for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.85,0:41:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是怕你将来后悔投资的太少.{\r}\NI just don't think it gets it done for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.36,0:41:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们先从9万美元开始算吧.{\r}\NWe'll do the $90,000 investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.69,0:41:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}公司总值估30万美元.{\r}\NAt a $300,000 valuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.99,0:41:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我需要你再投入25万美元作为贷款{\r}\NBut I also want you to kick in a $250,000 credit line
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.53,0:41:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}按10%的利息计算{\r}\Nwith 10% interest to be paid back in full
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.95,0:41:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}盈利后, 连本带利还你.{\r}\Nonce we meet net revenue positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.96,0:41:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.51,0:41:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说了, 好啊{\r}\NWhat I mean is, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.10,0:41:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是的.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.31,0:42:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 你们必须做的第一件事情是...{\r}\NNow, the first thing you need to do
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.48,0:42:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}正式成立公司, 这样你们两个创始人, 才能保护好自己的财产.{\r}\Nis incorporate, so that you two as owners can protect your interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.19,0:42:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当然, 前提是你们同意让我加入.{\r}\NAnd that is, of course, if you'll have me aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.53,0:42:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢, 马库拉先生.{\r}\NThank you very much, Mr. Markkula.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.91,0:42:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗯, 叫我麦克就好...{\r}\NOf course. Mike. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.82,0:42:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你好吗?  - 是的, 放那儿.{\r}\N- How're you doing? - Yeah, put her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.08,0:42:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 比尔.  - 比尔?{\r}\N- Bill. - Bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.41,0:42:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 费尔南德兹.  - 是的.{\r}\N- Fernandez. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.50,0:42:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 哦, 谢了, 麦克.  - 耶.{\r}\N- Oh. Thanks, Mike. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.08,0:42:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 你很厉害啊.{\r}\NSteve. Here's to you, pal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.47,0:42:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你有在听吗?{\r}\NAre you even listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.01,0:42:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我怀孕了.{\r}\NI'm pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.85,0:42:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 说话啊.{\r}\NSteve, you have to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.23,0:42:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这也是你的责任啊.{\r}\NThis is your responsibility, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.23,0:42:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你敢{\r}\NDon't you dare
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.61,0:42:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怪我身上啊?{\r}\Nblame this on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.74,0:42:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我没有.  - 呣呣.{\r}\N- I'm not. - Mmm-mmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.87,0:43:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们都有过别的...{\r}\NWe both had our moments of...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.75,0:43:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你指什么?  你究竟在说什么?{\r}\NWhat? What the hell are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.37,0:43:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你.{\r}\NYou.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.79,0:43:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我在印度的时候, 你有别的男人吧? 你懂得.{\r}\NWhen I was in India, you were with, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.09,0:43:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 你疯了吗? 你不能全赖给我啊.{\r}\NSteve? Are you crazy? You cannot put this all on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.84,0:43:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你现在不能把这事瘫在我头上. 现在不行.{\r}\NYou can't do this to me right now. Not now.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.72,0:43:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 对不起, 这不是你计划中的事.{\r}\NWell, I'm sorry this isn't part of your plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.14,0:43:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对不起, 那是你的问题, 不是我的.{\r}\NI'm sorry you have a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.94,0:43:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}问题不是我的.{\r}\NBut it's not happening to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.06,0:43:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 但, 这是你的孩子... - 不是!{\r}\N- But this is your... - No!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.40,0:43:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}滚出我的房子.{\r}\NGet out of my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.74,0:43:36.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 什么?  - 马上滚!{\r}\N- What? - Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.78,0:43:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 天啦. 终于到这一天了.{\r}\NOh, Jesus. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.34,0:43:54.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿. 你一切还好吧?{\r}\NHey. Is everything okay out here?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.76,0:43:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂文他要把我赶出去.{\r}\NSteven, he's kicking me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.76,0:44:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他不想与我有丝毫干系了.{\r}\NHe doesn't want anything to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.31,0:44:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}或许这样对你更好些.{\r}\NMaybe it's for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.69,0:44:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是他不应该这样对你.{\r}\NYou don't deserve to be treated the way he treats you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.11,0:44:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 我怀孕了, 丹尼尔.{\r}\NI'm pregnant, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.82,0:44:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么? 你有了...{\r}\NWhat? You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.53,0:44:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他说孩子不是他的, 但是我从没有外遇...{\r}\NHe says it's not his, but I would never...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.37,0:44:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我做错了什么?{\r}\NWhat did I do wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.75,0:44:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你没有做错什么.{\r}\NYou didn't do anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.92,0:44:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}错的是史蒂夫.{\r}\NIt's Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.17,0:44:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就是他错了...{\r}\NThat's just him.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.85,0:44:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他变了.{\r}\NHe changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.18,0:46:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}和你的电视机连接起来.{\r}\NHook them right to your television.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.27,0:46:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就是这样, 耶.{\r}\NIt is, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.40,0:46:24.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得怎么样, J? 准备好了吗?{\r}\NWhat do you think, J? Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.29,0:46:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}女士们, 先生们, 我是史蒂夫.乔布斯.{\r}\NLadies and gentlemen, my name is Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.13,0:46:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当我创立Apple的时候,{\r}\NWhen I founded this company,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.43,0:46:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我心中只有一个目标.{\r}\NI had one goal in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.80,0:46:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且没有人觉得这个目标可以实现.{\r}\NAnd that was to do what nobody else considered possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.89,0:46:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}(那就是)将世界最尖端科技的力量和艺术{\r}\NTo put the power and the beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.31,0:46:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}完美结合做成产品{\r}\Nof the world's most advanced technology
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.06,0:46:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}并将它带到老百姓的生活中去.{\r}\Nin the hands and homes of people just like you and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.44,0:47:03.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我保证, 从今天开始,{\r}\NAnd I can promise you that after today,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.28,0:47:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们看待电脑的眼光将彻底改变.{\r}\Nyou will never look at computers the same way again.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.20,0:47:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因此, 我自豪地想你们和泉世界宣布,{\r}\NSo I am proud to introduce to you, and the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.95,0:47:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是个人电脑的未来.{\r}\Nthe future of personal computing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.42,0:47:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}革命性的Apple II (苹果二代电脑).{\r}\NThe revolutionary Apple ll.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.96,0:48:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们得重来, 整个操作必须有直觉性,{\r}\NGotta just start over. It has to be intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.67,0:48:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}可预测性. 我是说, 在你们了解你将做什么之前,{\r}\NPrecognitive. I mean, I want it to know what you want to do
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.05,0:48:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们得让你的产品知道你将怎样对待它.{\r}\Nbefore you even know you want to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.01,0:48:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}等等, 我们还是在聊"命令栏"的事吗?{\r}\NWait, are we still talking about the command prompts?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.89,0:48:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比尔, 我们在谈所有的细节, 整件事情.{\r}\NBill, we're talking about everything. The whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.85,0:49:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"丽莎". 伙计们, 我现在告诉你们: 这个产品, 代表着未来.{\r}\NLisa. Guys, it's the future. I'm telling you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.81,0:49:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是说, "丽莎"在未来10年内将改变世界.{\r}\NI mean, Lisa's gonna do for the next 10 years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.77,0:49:06.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就像Apple II在过去3年里改变了世界一样.{\r}\Nwhat the Apple ll did for the last three.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.23,0:49:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我现在就可以这样说道.{\r}\NI can tell you that right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.65,0:49:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道人们为什么买苹果电脑吗?{\r}\NDo you know why people buy an Apple?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.32,0:49:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为什么买苹果电脑, 而不买我们竞争对手的产品?{\r}\NWhy do they buy an Apple, not the competitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.58,0:49:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为它(苹果电脑)很酷.{\r}\NBecause it's got bravado.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.75,0:49:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它代表社会地位, 让你成为时尚风标.{\r}\NIt's social status.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.58,0:49:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 你们知道怎么回事吗? 它甚至比这更重要.{\r}\NNo, you know what? It's even more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.08,0:49:23.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是社会流通货币.{\r}\NIt's social currency.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.08,0:49:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们提高了业界产品水准.{\r}\NWe've raised the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.05,0:49:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果我们想保持领先, 我们要勇于冒险.{\r}\NAnd if we want to stay there, we gotta risk everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.59,0:49:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}像狄伦, 毕卡索, 牛顿这样的伟大创作者, 他们都勇于承担失败的风险{\r}\NGreat artists, Dylan, Picasso, Newton, they risk failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.60,0:49:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们做大事, 就要敢冒风险.{\r}\NAnd if we want to be great, we've gotta risk it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.73,0:49:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为了一个命令栏,{\r}\NOn the command bar?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.90,0:49:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为了所有事情.{\r}\NOn everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.98,0:49:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 什么... - 从小事情开始.{\r}\N- What... - And it starts with the little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.23,0:49:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这里有20多个功能{\r}\NThere's over 20 different functions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.94,0:49:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}命令栏的改变虽小, 但是牵一发而动全身{\r}\Ntied to every single variation of the command bar,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.40,0:49:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}(就这小的改变)也要花好几个星期去编程.{\r}\Nwhich by the way, takes weeks to program.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.57,0:49:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不会重复IBM做过的东西{\r}\NWe're not doing anything that IBM's not already doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.70,0:50:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我相信我们的前瞻性{\r}\NAnd I would rather gamble on our vision
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.96,0:50:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}远胜于做一件雷同的产品.{\r}\Nthan make a me-too product.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.79,0:50:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们做出的产品虽然很小, 但是总是令人难忘.{\r}\NWe got to make the small things just unforgettable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.34,0:50:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}简而言之, 就是这款"丽莎文字处理器".{\r}\NLet's just start with something simple. LisaWrite.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.67,0:50:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我点击这些选单会出现什么?{\r}\NWhat happens if I click on one of these tabs?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.55,0:50:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}会有下拉选单, 让你能进入"参数设定"的界面,{\r}\NYou get a drop-down menu, and then there's preferences,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.22,0:50:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}和"页面设置"界面.{\r}\Nand page options.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.51,0:50:19.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 正是如此.{\r}\NOkay. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.09,0:50:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 点击哪个选单可以修改字体?{\r}\NNow, which tab do I click on to get different font styles?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.02,0:50:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"丽莎文字处理器"支持几种客户自定义字体?{\r}\NHow many custom typefaces are there on LisaWrite?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.49,0:50:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我正是我想跟你说的一件事, 史蒂夫, 那就是...{\r}\NThat's actually something that I wanted to talk to you about, Steve, is...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.20,0:50:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}几个月前我就要求你们弄出多种字体,{\r}\NI've been asking for the fonts for months.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.24,0:50:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你要求的东西都是概念层面的.{\r}\NBut everything we're talking about is conceptual.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.54,0:50:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对不起, 但是目前字体还不是至关紧要的事情.{\r}\NAnd I'm sorry, but typeface, it isn't exactly a pressing issue right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.38,0:50:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}每一件事都至关紧要.{\r}\NEverything is a pressing issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.01,0:50:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你想把"丽莎"所代表的未来变成现实,{\r}\NIf we want to make the vision for Lisa a reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.85,0:51:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你就要全心投入, 才能做出伟大的产品.{\r}\Nwe gotta put in the hours and make something great.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.27,0:51:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道, 但是这个软件做起来很困难,{\r}\NYeah, but we have a hard date on this software,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.39,0:51:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而且弄些漂亮字体还是于事无补.{\r}\Nand I'm sorry, but adding pretty fonts is not gonna change that.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.77,0:51:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比尔, 你说呢?{\r}\NWell, Bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.36,0:51:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你不能共享我们的热忱,{\r}\NIf you don't share our enthusiasm,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.70,0:51:20.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不认同这家公司的理念...{\r}\Nand care for the vision of this company...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.58,0:51:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不, 不, 不, 我只是不太我理解...{\r}\NNo, no, no, no. I just, I'm not understanding...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.37,0:51:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 滚出去.  - 什么?{\r}\N- Get out. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.21,0:51:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 要你卷铺盖走人. - 什么? 等等...{\r}\N- Get your shit and get out. - What, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.33,0:51:28.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你玩完了. - 什么? 你竟然...{\r}\N- You're done. - What, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.88,0:51:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么, 你难道, 你难道想炒我鱿鱼吗?{\r}\NWhat, are you gonna, you're gonna fire me?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.21,0:51:31.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不!{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.42,0:51:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我已经炒了你鱿鱼!{\r}\NI already fired you!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.92,0:51:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么还赖着不走?{\r}\NWhy are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.77,0:51:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 那是我们部门最好的程序设计师.{\r}\NSteve, he was our best programmer in the division.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.31,0:51:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个最好的程序设计师并不关心我们的公司理念.{\r}\NHe's the best programmer that doesn't care about our vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.86,0:51:53.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 我知道我不该说这些, 但是...{\r}\NOkay. Look, I know it's not my place to say it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.86,0:51:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那就闭上你的臭嘴, 比尔!{\r}\NThen shut the hell up, Bill!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.04,0:51:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.32,0:51:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 打扰了, 乔布斯先生.{\r}\NSo sorry to interrupt you, Mr. Jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.41,0:52:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你的律师8点就来了.{\r}\Nbut your attorney is here for your 8:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.74,0:52:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好.{\r}\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.04,0:52:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天下午我就要看到样本.{\r}\NI want to see samples this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.67,0:52:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们居然做了个没有字体的文字处理软件.{\r}\NSomehow we managed to design a word processor that doesn't have fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.71,0:52:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}再也不能这样了.{\r}\NAnd it can't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.47,0:52:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}赶快给我搞定!{\r}\NSo fix it!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.07,0:52:37.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}2点至3点. 你10点的安排的事情正等着你去解决.{\r}\N2:00 to 3:00. And your 10:00 is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.78,0:52:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫. 史蒂夫, 嘿.{\r}\NSteve. Steve, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.99,0:52:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}丹尼尔, 嘿.{\r}\NDaniel. Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.04,0:52:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}能跟你聊两句吗?{\r}\NDo you have a second to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.04,0:52:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我以为我们得重新预约吧.{\r}\NI thought we rescheduled.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.46,0:52:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就一会儿.{\r}\NIt'll only take a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.17,0:52:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家都这么说.{\r}\NThat's what everyone says.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.67,0:52:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.60,0:53:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧.{\r}\NFine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.97,0:53:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我还没吃午饭, 所以中午去"好地球"餐厅一起吃个便饭.{\r}\NI don't have a lunch, so, meet me at Good Earth at noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.31,0:53:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好啊, 没问题.{\r}\NOkay. Cool. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.60,0:53:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你最近负责什么工作?{\r}\NWhat are you working on these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.27,0:53:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 呃...{\r}\NOh, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.77,0:53:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}主要是Apple II电脑的维修手册.{\r}\NApple ll Plus repairs, mainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.36,0:53:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好.{\r}\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.62,0:53:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你得签这个.{\r}\NI need you to sign this.
