Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.73,0:56:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喝啤酒啊?{\r}\NDrinking a beer, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.36,0:56:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}明天是你的大日子.{\r}\NTomorrow's a big day for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.03,0:56:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们的大日子.{\r}\NFor us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.41,0:56:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗯, 我们的.{\r}\NFor us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.41,0:57:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克跟我说了你做的好事, 关于比尔, 丹尼尔{\r}\NMike told me about what happened with Bill and Dan
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.63,0:57:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还有克里斯. 好, 史蒂夫...{\r}\Nand Chris. And, Steve...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.47,0:57:12.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你为什么这么做?{\r}\NWhy'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.93,0:57:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}公司大了, 就对他们不管不顾了{\r}\NThe company outgrew them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.26,0:57:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们不是管理阶层. 他们也不是项目带头人.{\r}\NThey're not management. They're not project leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.81,0:57:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我的工作不是当好人.{\r}\NIt's not my job to be nice to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.48,0:57:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是为了让公司变得更好.{\r}\NIt's my job to make them better.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.48,0:57:23.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们不值那个价.{\r}\NThey don't deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.94,0:57:25.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那谁就值那个价了?{\r}\NThen who the hell does?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.90,0:57:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道公司怎么运转吗?{\r}\NDo you know how this company works?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.94,0:57:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想知道吗?{\r}\NDo you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.28,0:57:31.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你想知道, 我可以教你.{\r}\NI'd be happy to teach you, if you want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.07,0:57:37.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道我当初为什么跟你一起创办这个公司吗?{\r}\NDo you know why I started this company with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.41,0:57:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而放弃了惠普那个安稳工作吗?{\r}\NWhy I left the safety of HP for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.58,0:57:45.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你不知道吧, 你也没问过.{\r}\NI doubt you do. You never asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.42,0:57:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我离开那里, 因为Apple是我亲手创办的.{\r}\NI left because this was my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.09,0:57:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还因为你们这些家伙很酷.{\r}\NAnd you guys thought it was cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.26,0:57:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我只是想成为你们这帮酷男中的一份子.{\r}\NI just wanted to be one of the guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.60,0:58:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而你是最酷的那个人.{\r}\NAnd of all the guys I knew, you were the coolest.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.98,0:58:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你聪明而机灵{\r}\NYou were smart, quick-witted.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.53,0:58:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是我能以所好为生的机会.{\r}\NAnd this was my chance to do what I loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.95,0:58:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我为了乐趣而加入,{\r}\NAnd to do it for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.20,0:58:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是全部, 这就是我想要的.{\r}\NThat's all, that's all I ever wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.70,0:58:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我曾经以为这也是你想要的.{\r}\NI thought that's what you wanted, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.13,0:58:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你变了, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NSomething's happened to you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.05,0:58:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我长大了, 沃兹.{\r}\NI'm grown up, Woz.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.89,0:58:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不, 你还是个小屁孩.{\r}\NNo. No, you're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.79,0:59:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在播报今日头条新闻{\r}\NAnd now, turning to big news in business,
