Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.34,0:59:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 耶. 哦, 太好了.{\r}\NYeah. Yeah. Oh, terrific.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.39,1:00:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 你成功了.{\r}\NYeah, you did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.39,1:00:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}让我们一起把这股票做起来.{\r}\NLet's help them move that stock.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.06,1:00:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 伙计.{\r}\NHey, pal.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.69,1:00:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 嘿, 谢谢你.{\r}\NOh, hey, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.73,1:00:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}生意如常, 伙计.{\r}\NBusiness as usual, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.37,1:00:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大伙儿, 还有点工作要做.{\r}\NThere's work to be done, people.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.29,1:00:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你. 我有一些很好玩的点子.{\r}\NThank you. I had some fun ideas.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.75,1:00:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我就是我分内的, 比尔. 后会有期.{\r}\NThis is it for me, Bill. I'll see you when I see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.88,1:00:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要离开了.{\r}\NI'm gonna get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.38,1:00:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有空打电话给你.{\r}\NI'll call you later.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.67,1:00:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好的.{\r}\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.40,1:00:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨, 你能通知马库拉先生我们来了吗? 谢谢.{\r}\NHi. Could you please tell Mr. Markkula we're here. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.90,1:01:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好的, 洛克先生.{\r}\NYes, sir, Mr. Rock.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.95,1:01:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}先生们.{\r}\NGentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.12,1:01:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克. 请.{\r}\NMike. Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.96,1:01:13.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}坐吧.{\r}\NHave a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.34,1:01:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有些事情, 我们需要谈谈,{\r}\NThere's something we need to talk about,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.76,1:01:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}尽管我知道你不想听.{\r}\Nand I don't think you're gonna like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.34,1:01:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是关于史蒂夫的.{\r}\NIt's Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.97,1:01:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他在一个不切实际的项目上疯狂砸钱{\r}\NHe's hemorrhaging the company's dollar
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.30,1:01:27.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而这个项目用我们的丽萨电脑是搞不定的.{\r}\Non fantasies that simply are not possible with the Lisa computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.77,1:01:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但史蒂夫一直以来都善于化腐朽为神奇,{\r}\NYeah, but Steve's been doing the impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.81,1:01:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}从公司在车库里创立以来就是这样的.{\r}\Never since this company was in a garage.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.19,1:01:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克, 你知道我欣赏史蒂夫的一切特质的, 真的.{\r}\NMike, I love everything Steve represents. You know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.86,1:01:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但我们在放纵他, 让他成了任性的孩子.{\r}\NBut he's like a kid in a candy store, and we've given him the keys.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.36,1:01:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 但这是他的公司, 他爱谁谁.{\r}\NYeah. But, it's his candy store.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.16,1:01:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没有人见过这种电脑,{\r}\NYou're never gonna see a personal computer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.87,1:01:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}能把键盘和机身连在一起.{\r}\Nwhere the keyboard is attached to the machine again.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.16,1:01:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克, 问题很大.{\r}\NMike, it's a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.87,1:01:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}最大的问题是他还揶揄IBM公司.{\r}\NThe bigger problem is that he is ridiculing IBM.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.67,1:01:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}乔布斯他买断了华尔街日报的一个整幅版面{\r}\NJobs took out a full page ad in The Wall Street Journal
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.71,1:02:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}公然挑衅世界上最大的电脑公司.{\r}\Ntaunting the biggest computer company on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.51,1:02:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"恭喜你们终于做了一台个人电脑. "{\r}\N"Congratulations on your first personal computer."
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.55,1:02:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他这是要跟IBM开战啊.{\r}\NHe's trying to start a war with IB fucking M!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.77,1:02:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我看到这广告了.{\r}\NI'm fully aware of the ad.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.31,1:02:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那你还不阻止他!{\r}\NThen do something about it!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.73,1:02:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 亚瑟, 你知道他是对的.{\r}\NListen, Arthur, you know he's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.15,1:02:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}3年前, IBM对个人电脑根本没兴趣.{\r}\NThree years ago IBM had no interest in the personal computer
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.32,1:02:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在你看看他们的样子.{\r}\Nand now look at 'em!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.69,1:02:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在他们开始跟风了, 想想吧.{\r}\NThey followed us. Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.15,1:02:22.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们想好了, 麦克.{\r}\NWe have, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.74,1:02:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}令人抱歉的是, 董事会一致同意...{\r}\NAnd I'm sorry, but the Board is unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.53,1:02:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫不能再负责"丽萨"项目了.{\r}\NSteve will no longer be involved in Lisa's development. Period.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.04,1:02:32.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么回事, 亚瑟? 你们要搞权力架空吗?{\r}\NWhat is this, Arthur? Some sort of power play?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.21,1:02:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们支持他搞这个有一年半了.{\r}\NFor 18 months now you've offered nothing but support.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.83,1:02:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个节骨眼上要换掉他?{\r}\NAnd now you want to try and take Jobs off of his own team?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.55,1:02:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我也不想呀, 麦克.{\r}\NI don't want any of this, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.59,1:02:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你得考虑一下...{\r}\NBut you have to try to look at it
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.89,1:02:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}站在股东角度考虑一下.{\r}\Nfrom the shareholder's perspective.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.89,1:02:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫很棒.{\r}\NSteve is great.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.76,1:02:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他很棒.  是的, 他真的很棒.{\r}\NHe's great. Yeah, he's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.93,1:02:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但他是个定时炸弹.{\r}\NBut he's a time bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.23,1:02:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们的职责就是拆掉这颗炸弹.{\r}\NAnd it's our job to diffuse him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.73,1:02:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那你去搞定这事儿.{\r}\NSo take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.24,1:03:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我才不管董事会的狗屁想法.{\r}\NI don't give a shit what the Board thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.57,1:03:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你可以在别的项目上发挥专长了. 就是, 就是说...{\r}\NIt's the time you're taking. Your perfectionism. It's, it's, it...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.07,1:03:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}股东们一直盯着这产品,{\r}\NThey're looking at losses in the millions
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.74,1:03:11.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}自从立项以来, 我们就已经亏了几百万了.{\r}\Nbefore this thing even gets off the ground.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.54,1:03:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们看不到全貌.{\r}\NThey're not seeing the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.54,1:03:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没错, 股东们都是急功近利.{\r}\NThat's right. The shareholders don't see past their own shadows.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.17,1:03:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们只关心此时此刻.{\r}\NThey're only concerned about the here and the now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.05,1:03:22.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}董事会也同样"一叶障目不见森林".{\r}\NAnd the Board has got blinders on.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.92,1:03:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果他们的看法与你一致, 他们就不会吹毛求疵了,{\r}\NIf they could see you they'd take them off,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.09,1:03:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是他们的看法跟我对你的看法不同,{\r}\Nthey'd see you the way I see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.38,1:03:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们的看法跟你的同事对你的看法也不同.{\r}\NThe way your employees see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.59,1:03:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"丽萨"是我自己的项目.{\r}\NLisa is my project.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.55,1:03:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}它是我的.{\r}\NIt's mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.14,1:03:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}董事会就这样从我手里抢走吗?{\r}\NAnd they're taking it away from me?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.40,1:03:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你就让他们任意剥夺我的权力?{\r}\NYou're letting them take it away from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.27,1:03:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我靠, 史蒂夫. 你知道这不是事实.{\r}\NBullshit, Steve. You know that's not true.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.94,1:03:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他妈的.{\r}\NShit.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.41,1:03:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}和其它电脑相比较,{\r}\NThere are more Apple IIs teaching more subjects
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.38,1:04:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple II 电脑能教更多课程了.{\r}\Nin more schools than any other computer...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.09,1:04:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}小到学前班的识字课程,{\r}\NEverything from alphabet lessons for preschool,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.38,1:04:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大到大学的科学课程.{\r}\Nto science programs for graduate school.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.80,1:04:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}所以无论布莱恩想成为什么,{\r}\NSo whatever Brian wants to be,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.26,1:04:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一台苹果个人电脑{\r}\Nan Apple personal computer
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.60,1:04:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}总是可以帮他实现梦想.{\r}\Ncan help him be it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.63,1:04:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple II 电脑 - 只有你想不到, 没有它做不到!{\r}\NThe AppleII. There's no telling how far it can take you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.75,1:04:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}看起来毫无道理.{\r}\NNow that doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.25,1:04:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 你还没像我一样见到如此多的谋杀, 克罗斯先生.{\r}\NWell, you haven't seen as much of murder as I have, Mr. Cross.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.84,1:04:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我宁愿法官大人强迫我做这件事.{\r}\NI'd rather have a judge give me the works than have to do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.67,1:04:46.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就在这儿我独自承担.{\r}\NRight here in solitary.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.01,1:04:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那又怎样?{\r}\NSo what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.17,1:04:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那样的话, 你正还是在惩罚我. 你也脱不了干系.{\r}\NSo you go right on punishing yourself. You can't get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.31,1:04:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨, 我是格比.卡普兰.{\r}\NHi, I'm Gabe Kaplan.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.81,1:05:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}参加百事可乐挑战赛. 让你的口感决定一切.{\r}\NTake the Pepsi Challenge. Let your taste decide.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.44,1:05:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不错吧, 伙计们. 好了, 现在你们可以告诉我了{\r}\NRight, guys? Okay, now why don't you tell me
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.02,1:05:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们的选择. 百事可乐.{\r}\Nwhich one you chose. Pepsi Cola.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.28,1:05:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 喂?  - 史蒂夫, 我是麦克.{\r}\N- Yeah? - Hey, Steve. It's Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.36,1:05:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿.{\r}\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.53,1:05:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿. 我想我给你找到了一个不错的项目.{\r}\NHey. Um, I think I may have found a project for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.70,1:05:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是研发部门正在搞的一个项目.{\r}\NIt's more of an R&D outcast than anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.70,1:05:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是那实际上是你前一段时间批准的一个项目.{\r}\Nbut it's actually a project you approved some time back.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.08,1:05:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不如你去看看吧?{\r}\NWhy don't you look into it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.21,1:05:27.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是"麦金托什"部门.{\r}\NSo this is the Macintosh team.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.09,1:05:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呣-呣.{\r}\NMmm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.55,1:05:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 天哪.{\r}\NOh, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.18,1:05:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不. 只有史蒂夫.{\r}\NNope. It's just Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.55,1:05:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}见到你真高兴, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NIt's really good to see you, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.22,1:05:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比尔.阿特肯森. 很高兴他们得到了一员五虎上将.{\r}\NBill Atkinson. It's good to see they got A players over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.73,1:05:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呣-呣. 嘿, 起床.{\r}\NMmm-hmm. Hey. Get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.61,1:05:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 史蒂夫.乔布斯.{\r}\NHi, Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.28,1:05:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你叫什么?{\r}\NWhat's your name?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.40,1:05:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}伯... 伯勒尔.史密斯.{\r}\NBurr... Burrell Smith.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.07,1:05:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}伯勒尔.史密斯.{\r}\NBurrell Smith.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.99,1:05:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 有点乱.{\r}\NOh, sorry for the mess.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.11,1:05:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们就是一帮颓废青年. 因此...{\r}\NWe're just a bunch of degenerates. So...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.83,1:05:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没事, 我也喜欢颓废的苟活着.{\r}\NIt's okay. I like degenerates.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.33,1:05:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.29,1:06:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁是项目负责人?{\r}\NWho's your project lead?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.62,1:06:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 杰夫.拉斯肯...{\r}\NUh, Jef Raskin...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.83,1:06:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不知道他跑哪里去了.{\r}\NI don't know where he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.63,1:06:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}杰夫.拉斯肯.{\r}\NJef Raskin.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.46,1:06:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好. 我来处理. 现在由我负责了.{\r}\NOkay. I'll deal with that one. I'll be taking over now.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.51,1:06:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃...对不起, 你要执掌整个"麦金托什"项目?{\r}\NUm... Sorry, taking over, like, the entire Macintosh project?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.22,1:06:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 对.  - 太好了.{\r}\N- Yeah. - Awesome.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.85,1:06:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你的设计团队在哪里?{\r}\NWhere's your design team?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.61,1:06:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}团队? 我没有团队...{\r}\NTeam? I don't...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.40,1:06:31.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}让我看看进度吧.{\r}\NShow me your current build.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.78,1:06:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 显而易见, 简单易用是最重要的.{\r}\NWell, obviously ease of use is a big feature here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.45,1:06:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们想做一个很简单的用户界面.{\r}\NWe're trying to develop a simpler interface
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.16,1:06:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}主要是给一般用户使用.{\r}\Nthat's geared towards the real layman end user.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.29,1:06:46.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但使用者界面不容易整合啊. 说实话...{\r}\NBut, we're kind of struggling with the interface, and, to be frank...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.67,1:06:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们现在做的结果就是...{\r}\NThe results have been...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.67,1:06:50.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 一坨屎.  - 没错.{\r}\N- Shit. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.13,1:06:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}用什么零组件?{\r}\NWhat's it got under the hood?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.34,1:06:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}典型的配置,{\r}\NStandard kick ass stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.68,1:06:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}64KB记忆体...{\r}\NSixty-four K RAM...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.97,1:06:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}256色荧幕, 摩托罗拉6809处理器.{\r}\NTwo fifty-six bitmap display, Motorola 6809.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.60,1:07:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们准备使用68000.{\r}\NWe're gonna run the 68000.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.47,1:07:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是, 哥们, 那是"丽莎"的处理器.{\r}\NBut dude, that's Lisa's processor.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.98,1:07:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没错, 哥们.{\r}\NThat's correct. Dude.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.23,1:07:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不关心预算是多少. 给我那个处理器就行.{\r}\NI don't care what the budget is. Give me their processor.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.82,1:07:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}搞掂.{\r}\NDone.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.32,1:07:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NHey, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.19,1:07:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎样啊, 伙计?{\r}\NHow are you, man?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.12,1:07:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}克里斯, 很高兴见到你...{\r}\NChris, it has been a...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.28,1:07:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶.{\r}\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.53,1:07:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 你在这个部门做"麦金托什"?  - 是.{\r}\N- You're working on the Macintosh? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.70,1:07:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不错{\r}\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.75,1:07:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 这下有意思了.{\r}\NGood, this is gonna be fun.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.55,1:07:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 言归正传.{\r}\NOkay. Let's go back to what you were saying before.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.18,1:07:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是给一般大众用的, 对吧?{\r}\NThis thing is for the everyman. Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.43,1:07:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是我们的用户.{\r}\NThat's our end user.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.31,1:07:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}老师也好.{\r}\NIt's the school teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.18,1:07:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}清洁工也好.{\r}\NIt's the garbage man.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.64,1:07:50.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}小屁孩也好. 还是住在内布拉斯加州的老奶奶也好. 对吧?{\r}\NIt's the kid. It's some grandma out in Nebraska. Right?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.57,1:07:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们要把这东西做的非常简单.{\r}\NSo we need to make this thing simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.78,1:07:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就像一个...{\r}\NIt's gotta work like...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.87,1:08:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}家电那么简单.{\r}\Nlike an appliance.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.16,1:08:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 杰夫.{\r}\NHey, Jef.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.54,1:08:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫来了.{\r}\NSteve Jobs is here.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.79,1:08:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为你刚才不在...{\r}\NSince you weren't around...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.00,1:08:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}刚才我们领导层跟摩托罗拉的人开会呢.{\r}\NSome of the project leads were having a meeting with Motorola.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.96,1:08:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你来这里要干什么?{\r}\NWhy exactly are you here?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.34,1:08:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我来帮忙做好"麦金托什".{\r}\NI'm here to help build the Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.51,1:08:24.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不确定这是否可行.{\r}\NAh. I'm not sure that that's practical for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.14,1:08:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们可不想让这个项目{\r}\NWe're actually trying to avoid this project
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.14,1:08:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}也被某人毁掉.{\r}\Nbecoming another over bloated disaster.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.11,1:08:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 杰夫.{\r}\NOkay, Jef.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.41,1:08:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你引起了我的注意.{\r}\NYou got my attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.70,1:08:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NLook, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.25,1:08:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}项目开始的时候, 你不想帮忙.{\r}\NYou didn't want to be involved back when we started this thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.83,1:08:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我无所谓.{\r}\Nand that was fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.34,1:08:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你现在过来也好.{\r}\NI just wanted you to cut the checks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.75,1:08:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}只是加入就加入, 别把麦金托什{\r}\NBe involved, just don't turn Macintosh
Dialogue: 0,1:08:57.42,1:08:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当成你复仇的工具.{\r}\Ninto a measure of revenge for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.55,1:09:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家都知道你从"丽莎"项目被赶出来了.{\r}\NEveryone knows about your fallout with Team Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.81,1:09:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}相信我, 我们现在做的还不错.{\r}\NSo trust me when I say, we're doing fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.35,1:09:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}知道了, 杰夫.{\r}\NOkay, Jef.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.94,1:09:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我跟你这么说吧.{\r}\NLet's get a couple things straight.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.03,1:09:21.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不做得过且过的事情.{\r}\NWe don't do fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.53,1:09:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不安于现状.{\r}\NAnd we don't accept things the way that they are,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.08,1:09:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}创新不止, 勇往直前.{\r}\Nand we don't stop innovating.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.71,1:09:32.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你现在做出的产品, 毫无新意.{\r}\NNow, your machine lacks power.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.29,1:09:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现有的用户界面太小, 需要重新设计.{\r}\NAnd your little interface, it needs work.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.88,1:09:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我来帮忙把它做好.{\r}\NAnd I'm here to help with that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.84,1:09:40.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不是要抢走"麦金托什"项目.{\r}\NNow, I'm not trying to take Macintosh away from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.80,1:09:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我希望你留在团队里.{\r}\NI want you on this team.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.97,1:09:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你要么留下来, 要么立马滚蛋.{\r}\NBut you can either get on board, or you can get the fuck out.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.15,1:09:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好了, 现在我们还有很多正事要做, 所以赶紧干活.{\r}\NOkay. Now, we've got a lot of work to do. So, let's get to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.53,1:10:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比尔, 跟我来.{\r}\NBill, you come with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.07,1:10:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}行, 去干什么?{\r}\NOkay. Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.82,1:10:03.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}招兵买马.{\r}\NRecruiting.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.95,1:10:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}靠.{\r}\NShit.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.45,1:10:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 嗨, 史蒂夫.  - 帮我拿一下.{\r}\N- Hey, Steve. - Hold these for a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.71,1:10:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 行. - 谢了.{\r}\N- Yeah. - Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.25,1:10:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么了? 怎么回事? 你这是演的哪一出?{\r}\NWhat, what's going on? What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.59,1:10:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫?  - 你现在是"麦金托什麦"团队的人了.{\r}\N- Steve? - You're on the Macintosh Team now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.38,1:10:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么, 史蒂..."麦金托什"是什么?{\r}\NWhat, Ste... What's a Macintosh?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.05,1:10:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}安迪.赫兹菲尔德.{\r}\NAndy Hertzfeld.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.55,1:10:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听说你你有两把刷子?{\r}\NAre you good?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.01,1:10:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我需要非常厉害的人加入"麦金托什"团队,{\r}\NI only want good people working on Macintosh,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.14,1:10:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}说实话我不知道你是不是有这个本钱.{\r}\Nand I'm not sure if you're good enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.10,1:10:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你说什么?{\r}\NExcuse me?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.19,1:10:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}比尔.阿特肯森告诉我, 你有两把刷子.{\r}\NBill Atkinson says that you're good.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:37.02,1:10:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我? ...对头, 我也这么觉得.{\r}\NI... Yes. I think I'm pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.65,1:10:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得自己富有创造性吗?{\r}\NAre you creative?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.74,1:10:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我...我...我还可以吧.{\r}\NI... I... I think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.94,1:10:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}欢迎加入"麦金托什"团队.{\r}\NWelcome to the Macintosh Team.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.16,1:10:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}小屁孩, 你总是让我给你擦屁股救火.{\r}\NI'm tired of saving your ass, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.71,1:10:55.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你好这一口, 我也没辙.{\r}\NYou love saving my ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.12,1:10:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我需要我自己的工程师队伍.{\r}\NI want my own engineering team.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.92,1:10:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}想要谁你自己挑.{\r}\NYou can pick them yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.09,1:11:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还有别给我安排什么{\r}\NAnd I am done working under the gun
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.38,1:11:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}狗屁的项目截止期限.{\r}\Nof your ridiculous deadline bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.72,1:11:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}随时给你假期去跟大奶妹约会.{\r}\NYou might as well be asking for a date with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.55,1:11:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我也要这项福利.{\r}\NI want that, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.52,1:11:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没问题.{\r}\NDone.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.89,1:11:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谈正经的, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NSerious, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.65,1:11:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这什么意思, 史蒂夫? 这是什么绩效面试吗?{\r}\NSo what is this, Steve? Some sort of performance review?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.31,1:11:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你现在的IIE项目如何?{\r}\NHow are things going on the IIE?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.90,1:11:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}进展不错. 真的不错.{\r}\NThings are great. Really great.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.40,1:11:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你一定觉得超无聊吧?{\r}\NYou're bored to death, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.74,1:11:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 我快无聊死了.{\r}\NYes. Yes I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.24,1:11:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想来"麦金托什"团队和我一起打拼吗?{\r}\NYou want to come work with me on the Mac Team?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.66,1:11:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想让我进"麦金托什"团队吧?{\r}\NYou're trying to recruit me for the Mac Team, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.50,1:11:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好, 算我一个.{\r}\NOkay, I'm in.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.63,1:11:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你一定有难关想要克服.{\r}\NYou've gotta have a problem that you want to solve.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.59,1:11:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}或者有错误想要纠正.{\r}\NA wrong that you want to right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.38,1:11:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这必须是你的激情所在.{\r}\NAnd it's gotta be something that you're passionate about,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.63,1:11:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}否则你就不会有毅力坚持下去.{\r}\Nbecause otherwise you won't have the perseverance to see it through.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.76,1:11:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别跟我说什么这产品进度不能更快了.{\r}\NI don't ever want to hear you tell me that you can't make it faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.10,1:11:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是说, 上百万的人想买这款产品.{\r}\NI mean, millions of people are gonna buy this machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.81,1:11:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不能仅仅是仅仅盯住竞争对手,{\r}\NAnd we can't look at the competition
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.02,1:12:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们要比竞争对手做的更好.{\r}\Nand say we're gonna do it better.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.11,1:12:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们得盯住竞争对手, 同事要做到与众不同.{\r}\NWe have to look at the competition and say we're gonna do it differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.91,1:12:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在我们有机会做一个革命性的电脑产品.{\r}\NWe have an opportunity to build a revolutionary machine.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.91,1:12:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你一生会做很多事情{\r}\NAnd in your life you only get to do so many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.78,1:12:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}此时此刻, 我们把生命花在这件事情上{\r}\NRight now we've chosen to do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.45,1:12:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那就让我们做到极致{\r}\NSo let's make it great.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.32,1:12:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很棒.{\r}\NIt's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.70,1:12:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 我说错了.{\r}\NNo. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.87,1:12:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这超级棒的.{\r}\NIt's insanely great.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.50,1:13:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果可能, 还要再增加点内存.{\r}\NWe should try to get more memory into it if we can.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.05,1:13:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是还得保证按时完工.{\r}\NWe can still hit the timeline.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.97,1:13:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}来看一眼吧.{\r}\NTake a look at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.34,1:13:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"麦金托什"这个当初的小东西现在"失去控制"了, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NThis little Macintosh side project has gotten out of hand, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.22,1:13:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}变得太前卫了.{\r}\NWay beyond the pale.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.43,1:13:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"丽萨"就被你搞得定价超过1万美元了.{\r}\NFirst you created a $10,000 monstrosity with Lisa,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.98,1:13:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你已经在这个原本投资不大的项目投入了百万美元.{\r}\Nand now you've poured millions
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.90,1:13:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而这本来是个小部门的.{\r}\Ninto what was supposed to be a minor diversion.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.44,1:13:26.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你错过了多次送货日期,{\r}\NYou've missed multiple ship dates,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.69,1:13:29.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}此时IBM正在统治个人电脑领域.{\r}\Nand meanwhile, IBM is just purring along.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.07,1:13:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫...{\r}\NSteve...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.41,1:13:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}人们不像你想像的那样去用电脑.{\r}\NPeople don't use computers the way you think they do.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.49,1:13:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们应该怎么去给"麦金托什"做市场推广?{\r}\NHow are we even supposed to market the Macintosh?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.54,1:13:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不用杞人忧天.{\r}\NWe don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.29,1:13:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你给我挑出5个CEO候选人, 你该让我来挑选谁做CEO.{\r}\NYou give me five candidates for CEO. You're gonna let me choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.46,1:13:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说, 我们就找一个市场营销背景的人来{\r}\NI say we choose someone with a marketing background
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.42,1:13:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}帮助我们销售我们从未卖过的产品.{\r}\Nto help us sell what's never been sold.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.51,1:13:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在, 我想自己管理这家公司,{\r}\NNow, while I would like to run my own company,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.93,1:13:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克说服了我, 大家认为我还没准备好.{\r}\NMike has helped me understand that you don't think I'm ready.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.10,1:13:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没错, 你确实还不行.{\r}\NYes, because you're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.72,1:13:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.27,1:14:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要约翰.斯卡利.{\r}\NI want John Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.39,1:14:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰.斯卡利?{\r}\NJohn Sculley?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.65,1:14:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}百事可乐的总裁.{\r}\NPresident of Pepsi Cola.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.27,1:14:05.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}百事可乐公司很不错的人.{\r}\NThe Pepsi Challenge guy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.61,1:14:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他很聪明, 是市场营销的天才.{\r}\NHe's smart, he's a marketing genius
Dialogue: 0,1:14:08.90,1:14:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为了成功不择手段.{\r}\Nand he'll do whatever it takes to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.90,1:14:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 斯卡利可不好挖.{\r}\NSteve, Sculley is a tough get.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.82,1:14:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他是我们的候选人中最难挖到的.{\r}\NMaybe the toughest on our list.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.74,1:14:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你凭什么觉得你能把他挖过来?{\r}\NWhat the hell makes you think you can get him?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.74,1:14:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他凭什么离开百事可乐?{\r}\NWhy would he ever leave Pepsi?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:23.29,1:14:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为糖水卖的再好, 也不能名留青史.{\r}\NNobody remembers the world's best soda salesman.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.60,1:14:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要找一个我能相信的人.{\r}\NI need somebody I can trust.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.52,1:14:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你能做出完美的产品,{\r}\NYou can make a great product.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.07,1:14:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是你得让人相信--{\r}\NBut you have to convince people
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.57,1:14:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你卖给人们的东西比实际的还要好.{\r}\Nthat what you're selling is greater.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.66,1:15:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们销售的不是电脑, 我们销售的是电脑能实现梦想的能力{\r}\NWe're not selling computers. We're selling what they can do
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.00,1:15:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一种让思想变成现实的工具.{\r}\Nwith a computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.91,1:15:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一种为思想服务的工具.{\r}\NA tool for the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.63,1:15:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}女士们和先生们, 这工具{\r}\NAnd that, ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.00,1:15:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}才是意义深远啊.{\r}\Nis limitless.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.42,1:15:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为人们一直相信{\r}\NBecause people will never stop believing
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.47,1:15:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们能从某件事情获取更多,{\r}\Nthat they could get more out of something,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.14,1:15:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}无论是他们的工作, 婚姻, 金钱,{\r}\Nwhether it be their jobs, their marriage, their money,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.14,1:15:22.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还是他们的生活.{\r}\Ntheir lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.02,1:15:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们想要更多, 你们要把Mac往这个方向打造.{\r}\NThat's what you have to do with the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.81,1:15:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是对无所不能的电脑的信赖.{\r}\NIt's the belief in the limitless.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.94,1:15:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没有什么是不可能的.{\r}\NThe impossible.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.86,1:15:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不管你有什么样的梦想, 你总能实现它.{\r}\NThat no matter what you dream, you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.36,1:15:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而Mac电脑就能帮你达到梦想的毕岸.{\r}\NAnd Mac will help you get there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.41,1:15:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}几个月前, 史蒂夫来曼哈顿找我,{\r}\NA few months ago, when Steve was visiting me in Manhattan,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.45,1:15:44.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}问了我一个很重要的问题. 他问道:{\r}\Nhe asked me a very important question. He said,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.00,1:15:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"你想一辈子卖糖水吗? "{\r}\N"Do you want to sell sugar water for the rest of your life,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.33,1:15:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"还是跟我一起改变世界?"{\r}\N"or come with me, and change the world?"
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.18,1:15:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗯,{\r}\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.47,1:16:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}于是我加入了苹果公司. 谢谢.{\r}\NHere I am. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.70,1:16:27.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在是1984年.{\r}\NIt is now 1984.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.37,1:16:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}看起来IBM想要统治一切.{\r}\NIt appears IBM wants it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.00,1:16:35.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple是阻止IBM的唯一希望.{\r}\NApple is perceived to be the only hope
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.67,1:16:38.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}让IBM望洋兴叹.{\r}\Nto offer IBM a run for its money.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.72,1:16:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}蓝色巨人(指IBM公司)是否将独霸电脑业界?{\r}\NWill Big Blue dominate the entire computer industry?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.35,1:16:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不可能!{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.06,1:16:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}称霸整个信息时代?{\r}\NThe entire information age?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.89,1:16:48.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没门!{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.65,1:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}乔治.奥威尔的关于1984预言是否会成真?{\r}\NWas George Orwell right about 1984?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.98,1:16:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不会!{\r}\NNo!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.03,1:16:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天, 我们第一次在此庆祝{\r}\NToday we celebrate the first
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.24,1:17:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}"信息纯粹性管理"的周年纪念日.{\r}\Nglorious anniversary of the Information Purification Directives.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.83,1:17:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是历史上第一次,{\r}\NFor the first time in all history,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.91,1:17:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是一个纯理想主义的后花园.{\r}\Na garden of pure ideology,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.25,1:17:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}在此的每个工作者工作称心, 表现完美,{\r}\Nwhere each worker may bloom,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.50,1:17:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不受他人打扰.{\r}\Nsecure from the pests.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.59,1:17:17.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们的竞争对手公司的员工却牢骚满腹的工作到死.{\r}\NOur enemies shall talk themselves to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.10,1:17:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是历史上的第一次.{\r}\NFirst time in all history.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.43,1:17:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们就是应该.{\r}\NWe shall...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.44,1:17:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}引领潮流.{\r}\Nprevail.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.06,1:17:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}1月24日, Apple将发布"麦金托什"电脑.{\r}\NOn January 24th, Apple Computer will introduce Macintosh
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.61,1:17:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你就明白为什么1984不会成为"1984" (详见乔治.奥威尔小说1984){\r}\Nand you'll see why 1984 won't be like 1984.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.40,1:18:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}干得好.{\r}\NGood work.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.79,1:18:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 什么反响?  - 我都不敢相信.{\r}\N- Some response, huh? - I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.66,1:18:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 这就像一场革命.  - 是的, 它就是一场革命.{\r}\N- It's a revolution. - It's a revolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.99,1:18:27.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}苹果电脑真的改变了世界.{\r}\NThe thing's a game changer.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.33,1:18:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你超越了你自己, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NYou really outdid yourself, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.29,1:18:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 为什么不聊个电话联系一下呢?{\r}\NHey. Why don't you give me a call?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.37,1:18:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 一起吃晚饭.  - 好啊.{\r}\N- Grab some dinner or something. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.21,1:18:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 行.  - 我喜欢这样.{\r}\N- Okay. - I'd like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.88,1:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫.  - 亚瑟.{\r}\N- Steve. - Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.34,1:18:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}干得好.{\r}\NGreat job up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.51,1:18:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢.{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.76,1:18:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 我想让你知道: 我们一直都相信你.{\r}\NSteve, I want you to know that we believe in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.39,1:18:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道你懂的.{\r}\NI hope you know that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:50.22,1:18:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你, 亚瑟.{\r}\NThank you, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.40,1:19:03.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿.{\r}\NHey.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.20,1:19:05.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他想说什么?{\r}\NWhat was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.82,1:19:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么...{\r}\NWhat...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.99,1:19:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}若克. 他刚刚...{\r}\NRock. He just...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.20,1:19:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}说什么"我们一直相信你".{\r}\NSaid something, "we believe in you."
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.54,1:19:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}怎么回事儿?{\r}\NWhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.71,1:19:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗯, 他指的是"麦金托什"电脑.{\r}\NIt's the Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.04,1:19:16.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道, 这个项目太烧钱了.{\r}\NYou know, we had them run the numbers
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.63,1:19:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}尝试了100多种方法, 试了100多次...{\r}\N100 different ways, 100 times over...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.17,1:19:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 但是Mac电脑定价太高了.  - 是的.{\r}\N- You're marking up the Macintosh. - Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.05,1:19:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果我们照"旧"玩下去, 那么从产品发布之日就一直在烧钱.{\r}\NIf we keep it as is, we'll be hemorrhaging money by launch date.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.76,1:19:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不管, 你得让顾客买单.{\r}\NYou're gonna price out the consumer.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.05,1:19:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 我们没法做赔本生意.{\r}\NWell, we can't take the risk of flattening our profits.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.42,1:19:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不. 我们没法两全其美.{\r}\NNo. We can't have it both ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.43,1:19:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是说, 你还坚持使用最贵的硬件吗?{\r}\NI mean, you insisted on the most expensive hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.06,1:19:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Mac电脑的原本设计很便宜的.{\r}\NThe Mac was originally much cheaper.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.73,1:19:40.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}杰夫.热斯肯设计了一款售价1000美元的电脑.{\r}\NJef Raskin designed a $1,000 box.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.73,1:19:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我做了个更好的出来.{\r}\NI made it great.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.11,1:19:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你还想让公司继续盈利的话...{\r}\NIf you want the company to remain profitable...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.07,1:19:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是谁的主意?{\r}\NWhose idea was this?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.91,1:19:52.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家的主意.{\r}\NIt's a group decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.58,1:19:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是谁的主意?{\r}\NWhose idea was this?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.13,1:20:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我的. 不是麦克的, 也不是董事会的主意. 就是我的主意.{\r}\NIt was mine. Not Michael's, not the Board. It was me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.30,1:20:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别这么做, 约翰. IBM才做这种蠢事.{\r}\NWe don't do this, John. IBM does this shit.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.47,1:20:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫... - Apple不是这种公司, 我也不是这种人.{\r}\N- Steve... - Not Apple. Not me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.47,1:20:13.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别把我当作成坏人,{\r}\NLook, don't make me the villain because
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.22,1:20:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是在为公司利益着想.{\r}\NI'm looking out for our company's best interests.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.64,1:20:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.27,1:20:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有些事情必须要改变.{\r}\NSome things have to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.53,1:20:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你要是还执迷不悟,{\r}\NIf you keep heading down this path,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.74,1:20:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我也没办法保你.{\r}\NI will not be able to protect you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.91,1:20:33.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你跟那帮孙子一个德行{\r}\NThey got to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.29,1:20:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那帮孙子?{\r}\NThey?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.86,1:21:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你从哪里搞来的?{\r}\NHow'd you get this?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.82,1:21:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}昨天到货的. 很明显这是测试版, beta版都不算...{\r}\NArrived yesterday. It's pre-beta, obviously, but it's all...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.49,1:21:16.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是纯抄袭.{\r}\NIt's a blatant rip-off.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.05,1:21:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}给比尔.盖茨打电话.{\r}\NGet me Bill Gates on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.92,1:21:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我跟你明说吧, 比尔.{\r}\NLet me make this perfectly clear, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.47,1:21:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说完的时候, 你才能看穿这件事.{\r}\NSo that when I'm finished, you can still see through those
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.52,1:21:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你这个整天戴着近视眼镜的假文青, 就是无耻到极点的罪犯.{\r}\Nthick pretentious glasses, you psychopathic, unimaginative criminal.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.28,1:21:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你偷了我的软件, 我会向法院证明你是怎么抄袭的.{\r}\NYou stole my software, and I can prove it in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.70,1:21:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你赚的每一分钱我都要你吐出来.{\r}\NAnd I'm gonna sue you for every cent that you have ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.95,1:22:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我这辈子都不会放过你.{\r}\NAnd I will make it my life's mission to see to it that you never,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.58,1:22:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}永不.{\r}\Nnever,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.75,1:22:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你即使给我9成的分成, 我也不会让你赚到一分钱.{\r}\Never make another dollar that I don't first take 90 cents.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.93,1:22:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道大家都跟我一样不爽,{\r}\NI can only assume that you are all as irate as I am,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.43,1:22:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但你们都不愿意拉下脸来说狠话.{\r}\Nand you're simply too dumbfounded to speak.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.89,1:22:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}乔布斯说会生产一百万台,{\r}\NMr. Jobs promised us a million units.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.56,1:22:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在四分之一都不到.{\r}\NWe have yet to reach a quarter of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.48,1:22:25.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是时候做出改变了.{\r}\NSomething has to change.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:25.40,1:22:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}搞砸了两个项目, 研发费用超支,{\r}\NWith two failed projects, overextended R&Ds,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.61,1:22:29.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}还跟微软打官司,{\r}\Nand that Microsoft fiasco,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.28,1:22:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个季度我们会亏损, 有史以来头一次.{\r}\Nwe're about to experience the first quarterly loss in company history.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.78,1:22:35.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}IBM过去两年有比我们更好的产品{\r}\NIBM beat us to market by two years
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.82,1:22:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}销售业绩也比我们强.{\r}\Nwith a better product and better sales.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.24,1:22:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Mac连玩具都算不上. 简直就是个笑话.{\r}\NThe Macintosh is not even a toy. It's a joke.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.75,1:22:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}IBM准备要转型,{\r}\NIBM has now moved on to mini decks.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.96,1:22:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们也应该这样.{\r}\NAnd so should we.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.25,1:22:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你的意思是什么, 亚瑟?{\r}\NWhat are you getting at, Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.30,1:22:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}各位, 我想该重新定位,{\r}\NGentlemen, I believe it's time to reconsider
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.13,1:22:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}个人电脑的前景.{\r}\Nthe viability of the personal computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.81,1:23:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 有什么看法?{\r}\NSteve, anything to say?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.81,1:23:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想让我说什么, 亚瑟?{\r}\NWhat would you have me say, Arthur?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.11,1:23:11.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是你要提高定价的.{\r}\NYou raised our price.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.57,1:23:13.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别把怪到我身上.{\r}\NDon't put that on me.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.03,1:23:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}问题不在定价上, 史蒂夫. 问题是你的产品.{\r}\NThe problem is not the price, Steve. It's your product.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.12,1:23:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你把Mac定位太高档了,{\r}\NYou over-hyped the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.70,1:23:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}让顾客一等再等, 一直在给期待Mac的人画饼充饥.{\r}\NYou told people to wait. You sold the future of the Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.33,1:23:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}正因如此, 我们过去两年没有产品可卖.{\r}\NAnd as a result we lost two years of sales.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.58,1:23:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这不是我的错.{\r}\NIt's not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.00,1:23:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}总有人要来顶罪.{\r}\NWell, it sure as shit is somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.13,1:23:31.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃, 没有人支持我.{\r}\NWell, I'm not receiving any support.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.84,1:23:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你不给我资源,{\r}\NYou're stripping me of my resources,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.80,1:23:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}把大把的钱都投在Apple II上.{\r}\Nand dumping millions into the Apple ll.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.55,1:23:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道我们为什么在Apple II上投入那么多吗?{\r}\NDo you know why we keep dumping millions into the Apple ll?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.35,1:23:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为它很畅销, 我们七成的收入都来自Apple II. 但是Mac呢?{\r}\NBecause it sells. It's 70% of our revenue. How's the Mac doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.39,1:23:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说的很明白.{\r}\NI made my opinion perfectly clear.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.19,1:23:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你愿意像IBM一样做东西, 我没辙.{\r}\NIf you want to keep sucking on the tailpipe of IBM, then I can't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.02,1:23:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但我不会为某人的脑残的决策背黑锅.{\r}\NBut I will not take the blame for the failures of some court jester.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.53,1:23:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}够了, 这样说不太好吧, 史蒂夫....{\r}\NAll right, this is crazy, Steve...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.82,1:23:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不, 不. 你说谁呢, 史蒂夫?{\r}\NNo. No, no. To whom are you referring, Steve?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.33,1:24:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不知道, 亚瑟.{\r}\NI don't know, Arthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.04,1:24:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你说呢.{\r}\NYou tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.67,1:24:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰, 怎么不说话?{\r}\NJohn, you're awfully quiet.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.92,1:24:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊, 不好意思.{\r}\NYeah. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.59,1:24:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得无话可说.{\r}\NI guess I'm just at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.72,1:24:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}做市场的那个家伙. 百事可乐的营销天才{\r}\NHead of marketing. Pepsi genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.22,1:24:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在无话可说了.{\r}\NLoss for words.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.60,1:24:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是他的问题, 不是Mac产品的问题.{\r}\NIt's him. Not the Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.03,1:24:34.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是整个过程的代价...{\r}\NBut the cost of that process...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.07,1:24:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}1万美元的价签. 这个价签...{\r}\N$10,000 price tag. That price tag...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.17,1:24:55.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}去反对他吧, 不要拿Mac出气.{\r}\NGoes against him, and not against Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.96,1:24:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}挺讽刺的, 不是吗?{\r}\NIt's ironic, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.97,1:25:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你喜欢听巴布狄伦, 我喜欢披头士.{\r}\NYou chose Dylan, I chose, I chose The Beatles.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.64,1:25:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}披头士现在都过气了.{\r}\NSeems so backward now.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.60,1:25:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}沃兹.{\r}\NWoz.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.48,1:25:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你来这儿干什么?{\r}\NWhat are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.77,1:25:12.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很高兴见到你, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NGood to see you, too, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.56,1:25:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我...我有点忙.{\r}\NI'm... I'm a little bit busy.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.73,1:25:17.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}能等会儿再聊吗?{\r}\NJust, do you mind if we talk later?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.90,1:25:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 耶, 耶, 就一会儿.{\r}\NYeah. Yeah, yeah. This'll only take a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.70,1:25:23.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我, 呃...{\r}\NI, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.62,1:25:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 我要走了.{\r}\NI'm leaving, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.75,1:25:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}行.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.08,1:25:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 不, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NNo. No, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.75,1:25:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要离开Apple公司.{\r}\NI'm leaving Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.05,1:25:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}永远离开公司. 实际上, 我真的这么做了, 只是...{\r}\NFor good. Actually, I already did. I just...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.76,1:25:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我只是想该先跟你说一声.{\r}\NI thought I should come back and tell you first.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.55,1:25:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为什么{\r}\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.85,1:25:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们都明白这一天迟早会来. 我也说不清...{\r}\NWe both knew this was coming for some time. I don't even...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.69,1:25:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我都不记得上次我们聊天是什么时候了.{\r}\NI don't even remember the last time we talked.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.53,1:26:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那你想要我怎样?{\r}\NWhat do you want from me, then?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.11,1:26:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不是所有人都像你一样整天有的忙,史蒂夫.{\r}\NNot everyone has an agenda, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.28,1:26:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是啊{\r}\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.00,1:26:14.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道的--我还记得我们年轻的时候,{\r}\NYou know, I can still remember when we were just kids,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.29,1:26:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}在你老爹的车库里.{\r}\Nback in your dad's garage.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.30,1:26:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们只是想...{\r}\NAnd we just wanted to
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.63,1:26:24.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}为和我们一样的人们,做一些很酷的东西出来, 你记得吗?{\r}\Ncreate cool toys for people like us. You remember that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.64,1:26:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}记得{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.26,1:26:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在对你来说, 你不再在乎那些人.{\r}\NNow it's not about people anymore for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.43,1:26:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你只在乎产品.{\r}\NNo, it's about the product.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.10,1:26:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}最糟糕的是...{\r}\NWorst of all, it's...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.73,1:26:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你更在乎你自己.{\r}\NIt's about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.61,1:26:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你只在乎你自己的小宇宙, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NYou're the beginning and end of your own world, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.16,1:26:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这太狭隘了. 太伤感了.{\r}\NAnd it's so small. So sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.96,1:26:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得这样很孤独吧.{\r}\NAnd it's... it's gotta be lonely.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.17,1:27:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道你会说{\r}\NAnd I know you're gonna say
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.17,1:27:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}产品必须{\r}\Nthat the product and the person
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.59,1:27:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}满足用户的所有需求.{\r}\Nneed to be connected and all that,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.93,1:27:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但我觉得任何产品都无法达到你的要求.{\r}\Nbut it will never be what you think it will.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.22,1:27:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就是达不到.{\r}\NIt just won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.02,1:27:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}至少很长一段时间都做不到.{\r}\NNo, not, not for a long time at least.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.32,1:27:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不知道你脑子里在琢磨些什么, 史蒂夫, 但是我知道{\r}\NI don't know what you think is going on, Steve, but I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.57,1:27:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你很不好过.{\r}\NAnd it doesn't end well for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.57,1:27:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}其实我不想...{\r}\NAnd I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.91,1:27:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不想看你这么难受.{\r}\NI'm not sticking around to watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.29,1:27:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}往事如烟{\r}\NIt's been a journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.47,1:27:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想说{\r}\NAnd for the record,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.76,1:27:51.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我热爱我们之前做的一切.{\r}\NI love what we did.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.36,1:28:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 这是约翰斯卡利. 我不在, 请留言.{\r}\NHi. You've reached John Sculley. Please leave a message.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.45,1:28:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨, 约翰, 我是史蒂夫.{\r}\NHey, John. It's Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.74,1:28:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}呃...{\r}\NUh...
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.12,1:28:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我就...{\r}\NI just...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.21,1:29:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们还是好搭档, 约翰, 你和我.{\r}\NWe're still partners, John, you and I.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.80,1:29:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们必须同心协力.{\r}\NWe are, we're in this together.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.13,1:29:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗯...我...{\r}\NAnd I, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.47,1:29:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}记得给我回电话啊? 那是最好了. 呃...{\r}\NYou just give me a call back? That'd be great. Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.28,1:29:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嗨, 麦克, 我是史蒂夫.{\r}\NHey, Mike. It's Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.99,1:29:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}回个电话好吗?{\r}\NWould you give me a call back?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.16,1:29:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}拜托你了.{\r}\NPlease?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.71,1:29:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰, 你得夺权.{\r}\NJohn, you have to take control now.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.17,1:29:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道股东们已经快受不了吗?{\r}\NDo you have any idea how close our shareholders are to a panic?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.05,1:29:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们暗示你毫无作为?{\r}\NThe implications of your inaction?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.56,1:29:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}忘了你的责任吧, 公司都快完蛋了.{\r}\NForget your job, the entire company is at stake here.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.98,1:30:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大家会一起完蛋.{\r}\NThis could ruin everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.64,1:30:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道, 亚瑟, 但我觉得我们还能挽回.{\r}\NI know, Arthur, but I still think that we can salvage this.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.06,1:30:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么都挽回不了了.{\r}\NCan't salvage anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.69,1:30:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我怀疑...{\r}\NI doubt...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:06.98,1:30:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.86,1:30:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.40,1:30:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰.{\r}\NJohn.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.70,1:30:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.87,1:30:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}亚瑟.{\r}\NArthur.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.87,1:30:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么来这么早?{\r}\NWhat the hell are you doing here so early?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.33,1:30:20.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我也想问你们来这么早干嘛.{\r}\NI could ask you the same question.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.00,1:30:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}来的正好.{\r}\NThis is good.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.75,1:30:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 一起谈谈吧. 请坐.{\r}\NSteve, why don't you join us this time? Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.38,1:30:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在?{\r}\NThis time?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.67,1:30:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 坐下.{\r}\NSteve, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.56,1:30:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰?{\r}\NJohn?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:42.60,1:30:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 亚瑟, 我不想说.  - 你必须得说.{\r}\N- Arthur, I don't want to. - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.44,1:30:47.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你必须说. 开口吧.{\r}\NYou do. Say it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.70,1:31:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}把你刚才跟我说过的话重复给他听.{\r}\NTell him what you've told me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.33,1:31:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我发现我没办法继续工作.{\r}\NI find it increasingly difficult to do my job
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.92,1:31:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为前进的路上有很大的阻力.{\r}\Nwhen the greatest obstacle in my path
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.55,1:31:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我做事时, 暗中总有各种阻力作祟.{\r}\Ncasts a looming shadow over everything I try to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.94,1:31:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}再说一遍?{\r}\NWhat did you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.65,1:31:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫...{\r}\NSteve...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.40,1:31:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你别跟自己过不去了.{\r}\NYou are your own worst enemy.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.32,1:31:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}也别跟这家公司过不去了.{\r}\NAnd this company's.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.58,1:31:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这...真是难以置信.{\r}\NThis... It's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.30,1:31:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你以为你自己是什么东西?{\r}\NWho do you think you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.64,1:32:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是Apple公司的CEO.{\r}\NI'm CEO of Apple Computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.90,1:32:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}雇用你{\r}\NHiring you
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.90,1:32:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是我这辈子做的最后悔的事.{\r}\Nwas the worst mistake I have ever made.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.45,1:32:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 没必要闹成这样.{\r}\NSteve, it doesn't have to be this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.96,1:32:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 这样也好.{\r}\NOkay. That's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.33,1:32:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}董事会不能管理公司.{\r}\NBoards don't run companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.59,1:32:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}应该把公司交给创造产品的人来管理.{\r}\NThe people who create the product run the company.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.01,1:32:36.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他同意我们用512KB存储器.{\r}\NHe has the nerve to tell me we should have used the 512.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.51,1:32:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说我们要512KB存储器.{\r}\NWe told them that it needed a 512.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.84,1:32:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不能用128KB.{\r}\NWe said not to use the 128.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.84,1:32:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们知道128KB存储器根本不够用.{\r}\NWe knew 128 kilobytes wasn't gonna get it done when we built it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:43.18,1:32:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}斯卡利今晚会去中国,{\r}\NSculley is leaving for China tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.52,1:32:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}要待一星期, 所以我们还有时间.{\r}\NHe's gonna be there for a week, so we got time.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.85,1:32:49.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们得拉拢一些人.{\r}\NWe just gotta recruit.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.23,1:32:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 斯卡利会发现的.{\r}\NSteve, Sculley's gonna find out.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.86,1:32:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}然后会发生什么? 你懂的.{\r}\NAnd then what happens, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:53.19,1:32:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他现在可是CEO.{\r}\NHe's the CEO of the company now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.69,1:32:55.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那是暂时的.{\r}\NWell, for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.90,1:32:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}公司大多人站在我们这边.{\r}\NBut we have the people who make Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.61,1:33:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 嘿, 麦克,{\r}\NOh, hey, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.99,1:33:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们刚开始聊两句而已.{\r}\NWe're just getting started.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:06.37,1:33:08.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}兄弟们, 给我们几秒钟说句话.{\r}\NGuys, give us a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.38,1:33:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}约翰取消了去中国的行程.{\r}\NJohn's canceled his trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.47,1:33:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他明天就会召集管理层表决.{\r}\NHe's having an executive staff meeting first thing tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:24.72,1:33:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}所以我不是来参加"革命"的, 我只是来通风报信.{\r}\NSo I didn't come to join your revolution. I came to warn you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.48,1:33:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他铁了心{\r}\NHe wants to make absolutely sure
Dialogue: 0,1:33:31.23,1:33:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}要架空你.{\r}\Nyou're nothing more than a figurehead.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.52,1:33:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不给实权, 不给头衔,{\r}\NNo power, no title.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.65,1:33:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不给团队.{\r}\NNo team.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.74,1:33:49.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我还记得我们第一次见面时候, 你雄心勃勃.{\r}\NI remember thinking when we first met, um, that you were remarkable.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.42,1:33:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想做大事.{\r}\NYou wanted to do something truly great.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.17,1:33:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那时, 我也一样.{\r}\NAnd I did, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.88,1:33:59.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我现在还一样.{\r}\NI still do.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.59,1:34:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}大丈夫能屈能伸, 跟斯卡利妥协吧. 算我求你了.{\r}\NRaise the white flag. Concede to Sculley. I'm begging you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.26,1:34:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}决不可能.{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.72,1:34:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你赢不了的.{\r}\NYou can't win this one.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.10,1:34:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你跟谁一伙, 麦克?{\r}\NWhose side are you on, Mike?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.73,1:34:13.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你现在必须站好队.{\r}\NBecause there are sides now.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.52,1:34:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}要嘛跟我一伙, 要嘛做我的敌人.{\r}\NAnd you're either with me or you're against me.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.90,1:34:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}站在我这边, 麦克?{\r}\NAre you with me, Mike?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.07,1:34:25.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 史蒂夫, 我跟你一伙.{\r}\NYes, Steve. I'm with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.54,1:34:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那好.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.46,1:34:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.47,1:34:42.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}选约翰.斯卡利的人请举手.{\r}\NThose in favor of John Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.27,1:34:59.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}选史蒂夫.乔布斯的举手.{\r}\NAll in favor of Steve Jobs.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.33,1:35:12.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.71,1:35:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}每个董事会成员都必须表态.{\r}\NEvery Board member's vote must be accounted for.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.84,1:35:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克?{\r}\NMike?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.14,1:35:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}斯卡利.{\r}\NSculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.61,1:35:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我选斯卡利.{\r}\NI vote for Sculley.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.89,1:36:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}既然如此...接下来我们怎么做?{\r}\NSo, now what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.90,1:38:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple股价在过去的几年内一直下跌,{\r}\NApple's market value has eroded in the past several years,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.61,1:38:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这导致了前CEO约翰.斯卡利于1993年下课.{\r}\Nwhich led to the ousting of former chief John Sculley in 1993.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.41,1:38:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}埃迪.伍拉德, 前杜邦公司CEO,{\r}\NEd Woolard, former CEO of DuPont,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:43.42,1:38:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}加入Apple公司成为董事会主席,{\r}\Nhas joined Apple as Chairman of the Board.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.13,1:38:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple新CEO吉尔.阿梅里奥说变革迫在眉睫.{\r}\NNew CEO Gil Amelio says sweeping changes are necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:52.68,1:38:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}乔布斯的新软件公司-NEXT, 正在...{\r}\NJobs' computer software company NEXT, has entered into buyout talks
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.22,1:38:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}与他的老东家Apple谈收购的事.{\r}\Nwith his former company, Apple Computer.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.80,1:39:41.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 去叫醒Lisa问她想吃早餐吗?{\r}\NHey, will you wake up Lisa and see if she wants breakfast?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.56,1:39:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好.{\r}\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.27,1:39:46.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Lisa?{\r}\NLisa?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.94,1:39:51.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Lisa? 起来.{\r}\NLisa? Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.57,1:39:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想睡一整天吗?{\r}\NAre you gonna sleep all day, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.07,1:39:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 走开啦.{\r}\NOh, go away.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.61,1:39:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊? 快起来, 都十点了.{\r}\NWhy? I say all day because it's 10:00.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.99,1:40:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}起来, 我给你做早餐.{\r}\NLaurene made you breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.58,1:40:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不饿.{\r}\NI'm not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.04,1:40:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喂, 你不能整个寒假就这样睡吧.{\r}\NWell, you can't sleep all winter break.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.75,1:40:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我就这么打算的.{\r}\NYes, I can.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.59,1:40:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}瑞德! 瑞德!{\r}\NReed! Reed!
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.05,1:40:22.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别糟蹋花园了, 好吗?{\r}\NCan we not run in the garden? Please?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.10,1:40:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢了.{\r}\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.02,1:40:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你叫醒Lisa了吗?{\r}\NWere you able to get Lisa up?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.07,1:40:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊, 普通人类有这么多觉要睡吗?{\r}\NWell, how can a human being sleep that much?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.24,1:40:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}她...我不知道她算不算普通人类.{\r}\NShe... I don't know if she's coming or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.29,1:40:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我一会要去农贸市场, 买点东西什么的.{\r}\NI'm going to the farmer's market today. Just gonna get a few things.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.17,1:40:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你今天有计划吗? 要不要一起去?{\r}\NYou have any plans? You want to come with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.17,1:40:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么?{\r}\NHmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.55,1:41:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我问你今天有什么安排?{\r}\NI said do you have plans?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.39,1:41:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天?{\r}\NToday?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.93,1:41:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}喂, 吉尔.阿梅里奥(Apple当时的CEO)会过来谈谈.{\r}\NWell, Gil Amelio is gonna stop by.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.73,1:41:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}交接一些关于软件的事情.{\r}\NThey're transitioning in some of our software.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:13.77,1:41:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}行啊.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.36,1:41:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我...我就是帮忙而已. 他们需要一点帮助.{\r}\NI'm... I'm just helping them out. They just need a little help.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.20,1:41:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 伙计.{\r}\NOh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.83,1:41:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不爽了, 不是吗?{\r}\NI'm in trouble, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.87,1:41:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 我怎样做你才愿意回来?{\r}\NSteve, what can I do to convince you to come back?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.13,1:41:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你想怎么说服我{\r}\NWhat can you do to convince me
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.46,1:41:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不需要坐上"泰坦尼克"号那样的高规格待遇的, 吉尔?{\r}\NI wouldn't be boarding the Titanic, Gil?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.01,1:41:44.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为我知道你深爱Apple, 而NEXT公司只是你暂时落脚的地方.{\r}\NBecause I know how you feel about Apple. What NEXT could never be.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.97,1:41:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}再说, 想想你现在拥有...{\r}\NPlus, you know, considering that you now own
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.35,1:41:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}150万份Apple公司的股票.{\r}\Na million and a half shares of Apple,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:50.60,1:41:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我是大伙, 这可是一大笔投资.{\r}\NI mean, that's a tangible investment, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.27,1:41:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们这帮家伙一定快绝望了.{\r}\NYou guys must be pretty desperate.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.44,1:41:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}才没有呢.{\r}\NWe're not desperate.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.78,1:42:02.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Newton项目怎么样了?{\r}\NHow are things going with the Newton?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:03.66,1:42:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那是前任的蠢主意.{\r}\NLook, don't blame me for the failures of the last regime.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:06.29,1:42:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那个项目不能再烂了.{\r}\NIt's not as bad as you think.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.50,1:42:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你也看到了, 裁员了不少人,{\r}\NYou're overseeing massive layoffs.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.92,1:42:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple的股价又创新低了.{\r}\NApple stock just set another record low.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:14.84,1:42:17.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们4个月后就要破产清算了, 吉尔.{\r}\NAnd you're four months from insolvency, Gil.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:18.17,1:42:19.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我说, 你们业绩这么差...{\r}\NI'd say that's pretty bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.17,1:42:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 为了保证公司还能运转下去{\r}\NWell, yeah. In order to fix what's broken,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.39,1:42:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们得做出一些牺牲, 对吧?{\r}\Nsome sacrifices are necessary. All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.68,1:42:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 你到底怎么才肯回来?{\r}\NSteve, what do you need?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.22,1:42:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}任何条件我都答应.{\r}\NName it.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.46,1:42:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫.  - 吉尔.{\r}\N- Steve. - Gil.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.25,1:42:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.46,1:43:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.97,1:43:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很高兴见到你.{\r}\NIt's nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.22,1:43:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}来, 带你参观一下.{\r}\NCome on, I'll show you around.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.64,1:43:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 吉尔, 不用担心. 我带他逛一圈.{\r}\NNo, Gil, don't worry about it. I'll give him the tour.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.27,1:43:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你确定?{\r}\NYou sure?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.35,1:43:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 必须的, 绝对没问题. 放马过来.{\r}\NYeah, sure. No problem. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.90,1:43:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那就好.{\r}\NThat's great.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.90,1:43:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}去吧, 你们好好逛. 我...{\r}\NYou guys go ahead. I'll...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:22.99,1:43:24.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我一会就去找你们.{\r}\NI'll catch up.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.32,1:43:28.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 有些事得跟你说清楚.{\r}\NThere's something I always wanted you to know, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.49,1:43:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当初赶你走, 不是我的决定.{\r}\NIt was never my call.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.62,1:43:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别提跑哪破事儿了, 麦克.{\r}\NLet's not do this, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.96,1:43:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 这事很重要. 你知道的, 当时我努力了.{\r}\NNo, this is important. You know, I tried.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.84,1:43:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我挺你的的. 我一直是这样做的.{\r}\NI wanted you here. I always did.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.71,1:43:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我费了好长时间才把你弄回来.{\r}\NIt's too bad it took me so long to get you back.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.51,1:43:46.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不, 我还没回来啊.{\r}\NOh, I'm not back.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.68,1:43:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}耶, 你会回来的.{\r}\NYeah. You will be.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.22,1:43:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们拭目以待吧.{\r}\NWe'll see about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.52,1:43:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好了, 我自己逛逛就好.{\r}\NYou know, I'm gonna show myself around.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.15,1:43:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我从这儿开始.{\r}\NI'll take it from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.78,1:44:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}贱人一个.{\r}\NSon of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.73,1:44:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这谁设计的?{\r}\NWho did these?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.53,1:44:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是我, 先生.{\r}\NI did, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:49.78,1:44:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你叫什么?{\r}\NWho are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.78,1:44:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}强纳生.伊夫. 我是工业设计主管.{\r}\NJonathan Ive. I'm Director of Industrial Design.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.00,1:44:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你怎么还在这里?{\r}\NWhy are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.08,1:45:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在是周一上午11点(上班时间)啊.{\r}\NIt's 11:00 a.m. on a Monday.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.09,1:45:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不.{\r}\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.67,1:45:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我问你为什么还待在Apple公司?{\r}\NWhy are you still here at Apple?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.80,1:45:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我创立的Apple公司不是这样的.{\r}\NThis isn't the company I built.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.22,1:45:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没品位, 没格调.{\r}\NThere's no taste, no style.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.02,1:45:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}没什么设计可言.{\r}\NNo design.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:16.93,1:45:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}除非有什么让你驻足不前, 你为什么要留在这样的地方?{\r}\NSo unless they're shackling you here, why do you stay?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.86,1:45:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哎, 先生, 我想其实还有一群人,{\r}\NWell, sir, I guess I would say there are still
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.28,1:45:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}始终相信Apple的理念.{\r}\Nthose of us that believe in what Apple stood for.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.24,1:45:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你所倡导的理念.{\r}\NWhat you stood for.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.62,1:45:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得我倡导什么理念?{\r}\NWhat do you think I stood for?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.29,1:45:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得...{\r}\NI think...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.42,1:45:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得, 你相信Apple的使命, 是让电脑,{\r}\NI think you believe that the computer,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.80,1:45:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}随身听或者类似设备{\r}\Nor the Walkman, or whatever it may be,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.76,1:45:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}成为个人生活的自然延伸.{\r}\Nshould be a natural extension of the individual.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:54.47,1:45:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}正是这种使命,{\r}\NAnd it's that mission,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:56.72,1:46:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这种追求完美质量, 还有创新点子和心灵感动的激情...{\r}\Nthat devotion to quality, and ideals, and heart...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.32,1:46:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就是我们留在这里的原因. 也许我们还有机会东山再起.{\r}\NThat's what keeps us here. That we might do it once more.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.48,1:46:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好. 甭管你现在在做什么,{\r}\NOkay. Whatever you're working on,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.52,1:46:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们要把现在这些设计全都忘掉.{\r}\Nthe rest of the day I want you to forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.32,1:46:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要每个人重新开始, 设计点新东西出来.{\r}\NI want everyone to design something new.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.90,1:46:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我不在乎它是什么, 是不是高科技产品,{\r}\NI don't care what it is, I don't care if it's technology,
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.07,1:46:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就尽管去创造吧.{\r}\Njust create something.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.70,1:46:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}做些更有用的东西.{\r}\NSomething useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.29,1:47:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}做些你真正在乎的东西.{\r}\NSomething you care about.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.63,1:47:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.34,1:47:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你回来了我们真高兴.{\r}\NWe're glad you're back.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.89,1:47:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我还没真的回来呢.{\r}\NI'm not back.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.77,1:47:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}暂时没有.{\r}\NYet.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.82,1:47:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫.{\r}\NSteve.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.71,1:47:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊!{\r}\NUgh!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.63,1:47:47.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}垃圾货.{\r}\NJunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.88,1:47:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫, 这是我们的董事会主席埃迪.伍拉德.{\r}\NSteve, you met our Chairman, Ed Woolard.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.30,1:47:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 史蒂夫 - 你好.{\r}\N- Steve. - Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.63,1:47:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 呃...{\r}\NLook, um...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.97,1:47:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我知道你之前被坑的很惨.{\r}\NI know all about the bad blood you must taste.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.97,1:48:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}知道你不会轻易地相信我.{\r}\NAnd I understand your hesitation to trust me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.92,1:48:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我只想说{\r}\NBut I just want you to know
Dialogue: 0,1:48:06.10,1:48:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我跟之前那位主席亚瑟.若克不一样. 我是你的朋友.{\r}\NI am not Arthur Rock. I'm your friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:11.57,1:48:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好啊.{\r}\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.19,1:48:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因此, 我们能聊两句吗?{\r}\NSo, can we take a minute to talk?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.49,1:48:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好啊.{\r}\NApparently.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.70,1:48:19.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天的报纸.{\r}\NToday's paper.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.41,1:48:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我相信你看了新闻了.{\r}\NI'm sure you've seen the news.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.37,1:48:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}对不起, 埃迪, 你具体一点最好.{\r}\NI'm sorry, Ed, you're gonna have to be more specific.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:26.04,1:48:30.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一夜之间, 我们的股价大跌7.5%.{\r}\NOur shares dropped 7.5% overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.00,1:48:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}跌到十年来的最低点.{\r}\NIt's the lowest it's been in 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:33.21,1:48:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}上周有个匿名投资者{\r}\NLast week an unidentified investor
Dialogue: 0,1:48:36.38,1:48:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}狂抛了150万股.{\r}\Ndropped one point five million shares.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:40.01,1:48:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}股民都恐慌了, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NPut a real scare into the marketplace, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:43.68,1:48:46.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}150万股这么多啊? 哈.{\r}\NOne point five million shares? Wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.90,1:48:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想, 我们的股民都吓疯了吧.{\r}\NI guess the stockholders must be getting restless.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:53.78,1:48:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们想让你回来, 史蒂夫.{\r}\NWe want you here, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:55.82,1:48:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我已经回来了, 是你们的顾问了.{\r}\NI'm here. As a consultant.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.78,1:49:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们想让你重回CEO宝座{\r}\NAs CEO.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.45,1:49:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- CEO?  - 没错.{\r}\N- CEO? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:03.79,1:49:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}起码先试用一阵子.{\r}\NAt least in the interim.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:06.29,1:49:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那吉尔呢?{\r}\NAnd Gil?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.54,1:49:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}啊, 他? 吉尔快要下台了.{\r}\NYeah, well, Gil's halfway out the door.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.88,1:49:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他也知道自己不行,{\r}\NHe has to see the writing on the wall.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:12.21,1:49:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他就是爱面子还在死撑.{\r}\NAt least if he's not too proud to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:14.51,1:49:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}哦, 他(麦克)会想办法把吉尔搞走, 找个机会让你出山.{\r}\NOh, he's going to try to force you out, and make a case against you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:18.68,1:49:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我以前在哪儿见过这种手段(指之前把史蒂夫挤出Apple的事情)?{\r}\NWhere have I seen this before?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:21.39,1:49:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}吉尔有潜在危险, 他没有筹码了, 很快就会走人.{\r}\NGil's on the ledge. He doesn't have a play here.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:23.56,1:49:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们只需要你一点稍微肯定的答复.{\r}\NAll we need is a little push from you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.39,1:49:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果你想夺回失去的公司, 现在正是天赐良机.{\r}\NIf you want to get back what you lost, this is the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.40,1:49:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我没有失去它, 它是被偷走的.{\r}\NI never lost it. It was stolen from me.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.41,1:49:46.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}电脑一点都不性感, 没有曲线美.{\r}\NThere's no sex left in computers. No curves.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:47.33,1:49:50.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果说电脑是艺术和美结合的产物,{\r}\NNow, if computers are for art, and beauty,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.54,1:49:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}并用来连接全球的每个人, 为什么现在的电脑都这么丑?{\r}\Nand global interconnectivity, why are they so ugly?
Dialogue: 0,1:49:54.80,1:49:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道的, 电脑应该是有艺术感的, 但是没有人在意这些.{\r}\NYou know, it should be artful. But no one cares.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.63,1:50:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}人们对电脑的印象都是非黑即白那么刻板,{\r}\NThe world may mistakenly see computers only in black and white,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.64,1:50:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是, 我们的生活, 我们的梦想, 我们的颜色, 都是五彩缤纷的.{\r}\Nbut we live, and we dream and we paint in color.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.23,1:50:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}电脑也应该是这样.{\r}\NAnd we think the computer should, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.28,1:50:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得怎么样?{\r}\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:25.99,1:50:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}强尼, 你一定要对我开诚布公.{\r}\NJony, I always want you to be honest with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:32.92,1:50:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不论发生什么,{\r}\NNo matter what.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.25,1:50:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一定要对我实话实说.{\r}\NJust be brutally honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.97,1:50:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}明白吗?{\r}\NUnderstand?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:41.68,1:50:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我明白.{\r}\NUnderstand.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.76,1:50:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你自己觉得呢?{\r}\NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:49.43,1:50:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我觉得, 这个蓝色,{\r}\NI think, I think the blue,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.52,1:50:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不是很满意.{\r}\Nit's not quite right.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:58.11,1:51:01.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这有个傻主意. 把音响内建到机器里面怎么样?{\r}\NHere's a dopey idea. What if we put the speakers inside?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.70,1:51:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别逗了, 史蒂夫, 吉尔和董事会{\r}\NYeah, Steve, Gil Amelio and the board
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.99,1:51:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不可能批准. 没门.{\r}\Nare not gonna allow that. No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.29,1:51:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们才不管他们批不批准,{\r}\NWe're not gonna ask for permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.34,1:51:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫帮了我很多忙{\r}\NSteve's done an admirable job assisting me
Dialogue: 0,1:51:18.38,1:51:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}尤其在他当顾问这段时间.{\r}\Nas an advisor during this, this period.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.30,1:51:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他的执行力和创造力没得说.{\r}\NAnd while I commend his actions, and his initiatives,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.60,1:51:29.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我相信, 现在是时候做进一步的调整.{\r}\NI believe it's now in our best interest to move on,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:30.06,1:51:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}今天起, 史蒂夫将不再担任顾问一职.{\r}\Nand relieve Steve of his advisory role in this company.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.40,1:51:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我同意, 吉尔.{\r}\NI agree, Gil.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.98,1:51:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是吗{\r}\NYou do?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:39.15,1:51:43.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}是, 我也认为史蒂夫不应该继续留在现在的职位{\r}\NI do think it's time Steve step out of his current role, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.11,1:51:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}史蒂夫?{\r}\NSteve?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.78,1:51:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢你, 埃迪.{\r}\NThank you, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.45,1:51:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我想跟董事会分享一下, 我对Apple未来的规划.{\r}\NI'd like to present the Board my vision for the future of Apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:53.83,1:51:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们不是微软或者戴尔.{\r}\NWe're not Microsoft or Dell.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:56.67,1:51:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}所以, 不要再学他们了.{\r}\NSo we need to stop trying to be that.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.17,1:52:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们需要回头看看我们的根本, 我们的强项.{\r}\NWe need to go back to who we are, and what we do best,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:06.47,1:52:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}其他的抛开不要管.{\r}\Nand throw away everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.39,1:52:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们擅长做电脑,{\r}\NHere's how we're gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:10.51,1:52:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们要建立新的电脑产品线{\r}\NWe're gonna build a new line of computers
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.39,1:52:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}家用和商用都要兼顾{\r}\Nfor the home, and for the office.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.02,1:52:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们要以NEXT为基础, 做一个全新的操作系统.{\r}\NWe're gonna build a new operating system on the backbone of NEXT.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:19.44,1:52:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这就是下一代的"麦金托什".{\r}\NThe next generation of Macintosh.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:22.23,1:52:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们打算砍掉所有其他的项目,{\r}\NAnd we're gonna kill every other project.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.99,1:52:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}全部砍掉.{\r}\NEverything.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:27.20,1:52:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这个公司, 决不能再出现屎一样的产品.{\r}\NThis company will not make shit anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.70,1:52:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们要扩大广告预算.{\r}\NWe're also gonna double down on the advertising budget.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.16,1:52:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Charite 是我们唯一的御用广告公司.{\r}\NChiat Day will be the only advertising agency we use.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.83,1:52:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就像过去一样.{\r}\NJust like back in the old days.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.54,1:52:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}简而言之,{\r}\NIn short,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.05,1:52:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们打算把Apple做得跟以前一样酷.{\r}\Nwe're gonna make Apple cool again.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:46.30,1:52:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当然, 我可能没法重振Apple{\r}\NBut I will not be able to move forward
Dialogue: 0,1:52:49.55,1:52:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}如果董事会的全体成员不给我运营自主权的话.{\r}\Nwithout the Board's permission to operate under complete autonomy.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:54.85,1:52:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我要成为董事会的全权投票成员. 最后一点是...{\r}\NI'll be made a full voting member of the Board. And lastly...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:01.48,1:53:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}临时CEO.{\r}\NInterim CEO.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.07,1:53:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}嘿, 等等.{\r}\NNow, hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.82,1:53:11.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我才是CEO, 你们这是...{\r}\NI'm the CEO, and this is...
Dialogue: 0,1:53:13.87,1:53:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}听着, 是你们逼我到这个地步的.{\r}\NLook, you put me in this position.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.62,1:53:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}Apple公司就像一条破船, 底部有洞, 正在漏水,{\r}\NApple is like a ship with a hole in the bottom, and it's leaking water.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:21.08,1:53:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}而我是船长, 我的工作就是负责...{\r}\NAnd it's my job to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,1:53:23.13,1:53:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}把船带往正确的方向.{\r}\Nwe point the ship in the right direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.30,1:53:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们为什么不让我继续干呢?{\r}\NSo why don't you let me do my job?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.43,1:53:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好吧, 我们还是来投票表决吧.{\r}\NAll right, let's put this to a vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.05,1:53:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谁同意史蒂夫来掌权?{\r}\NThose in favor?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.56,1:53:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你们搞什么鬼?{\r}\NWhat the hell?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:44.36,1:53:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}埃迪?{\r}\NEd?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:47.57,1:53:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克?{\r}\NMike?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.20,1:53:52.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 吉尔. 对事不对人.{\r}\NSorry, Gil. Nothing personal.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.92,1:54:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你在成长过程中, 会有人告诉你,{\r}\NWhen you grow up, you tend to get told
Dialogue: 0,1:54:04.80,1:54:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}世事如棋, 但江湖险恶.{\r}\Nthe world is the way that it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.96,1:54:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你的生活就是在社会上混日子{\r}\Nyour life is just to live your life inside the world
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.43,1:54:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不要太执着, 不撞南墙不回头.{\r}\Nand try not to bash into the walls too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.68,1:54:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是生命有限.{\r}\NBut that's a very limited life.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:17.27,1:54:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}生活的道路可以变得很宽广,{\r}\NLife can be much broader,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:19.27,1:54:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你只需要明白一点, 就是...{\r}\Nonce you discover one simple fact.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:23.11,1:54:25.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}围绕你的一切{\r}\NAnd that is that everything around you
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.86,1:54:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}即所谓的现实生活{\r}\Nthat you call life
Dialogue: 0,1:54:27.69,1:54:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}都是一群比你蠢的人为了愚弄你而编造出来的东西.{\r}\Nwas made up by people that are no smarter than you.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.45,1:54:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你可以改变它, 影响它.{\r}\NAnd you can change it. You can influence it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.49,1:54:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你可以走你自己的路, 让别人去跟风.{\r}\NYou can build your own things, that other people can use.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.16,1:54:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}别管那些错误连篇的胡扯, 例如:{\r}\NIt's to shake off this erroneous notion
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.54,1:54:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么"生活就在那里, 不离不弃",{\r}\Nthat life is just there,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.04,1:54:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么"活在当下", 什么"不能反抗, 就享受生活"之类的.{\r}\Nand you're just gonna live in it, versus embrace it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.79,1:54:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你应该改变生活, 改善生活, 让自己的生活与众不同.{\r}\NChange it. Improve it. Make your mark upon it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:49.55,1:54:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}只要你学会了这点, 你就不会成为凡夫俗子.{\r}\NAnd once you learn that, you'll never be the same again.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.72,1:54:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但是我们的现金流状况...{\r}\NBut in our cash position...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:57.68,1:54:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}CEO先生.{\r}\NMr. CEO.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:59.77,1:55:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:00.93,1:55:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你找我吗?{\r}\NYou wanted to talk to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.15,1:55:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}欢迎. 请坐吧.{\r}\NWelcome. Please. Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:05.98,1:55:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}- 埃迪.  - 嘿, 戈热斯.{\r}\N- Ed. - Hey, Gareth.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.23,1:55:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}麦克.{\r}\NMike.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:13.78,1:55:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}这是什么?{\r}\NWhat's this?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.53,1:55:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}一个机会.{\r}\NIt's an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:18.99,1:55:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我很久没见到伯纳德(Apple的法律顾问)了.{\r}\NI haven't seen Bernard around for a few days.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:21.54,1:55:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}凯瑟琳和德拉诺去哪儿了?{\r}\NWhere's Katherine, Delano?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:23.92,1:55:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}刘易斯先生和哈德逊夫人(即:德拉诺和凯瑟琳, Apple的两位董事会成员), 做了艰难而轻松的决定:{\r}\NMr. Lewis and Mrs. Hudson made a difficult decision easier
Dialogue: 0,1:55:27.79,1:55:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}很通情达理地退出董事会了.{\r}\Nby agreeing to step down from the Board.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:30.51,1:55:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}真的吗?{\r}\NReally?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:31.59,1:55:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他俩都接受了一笔可观的高管遣散费("金保护伞"费).{\r}\NThey both agreed to accept incredibly generous golden parachutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:36.39,1:55:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}同样的机会给你, 细节在信封里面.{\r}\NThe same opportunity is detailed inside that envelope.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:40.52,1:55:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}所以你要把我们赶走?{\r}\NSo you're forcing us out?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.81,1:55:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我这么做事出有因.{\r}\NWith good reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:43.98,1:55:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}什么原因?{\r}\NAnd what's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:45.19,1:55:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}当前的形势对公司的发展是{\r}\NThe current arrangement is
Dialogue: 0,1:55:48.27,1:55:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不利的.{\r}\Ninhibiting.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:50.40,1:55:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我没办法拖着累赘前进, 麦克.{\r}\NI can't hold everyone's hand while we cross the street, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.07,1:55:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}所以你的下一步举措就是直接干掉董事会?{\r}\NAnd so your next big move is to eradicate your Board?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.95,1:55:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你觉得这可行吗?{\r}\NAnd you think you can just do that?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.53,1:56:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}不好意思, 麦克. 是时候这样做了.{\r}\NI'm sorry, Mike. But it's time.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:02.25,1:56:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}拿着这笔高管遣散费吧, 这回报绝对赚到了.{\r}\NTake the parachute. It's more than fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:12.96,1:56:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}20年了{\r}\NTwenty years.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.43,1:56:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你知道吗, 我告诉过我自己: 我在这儿...{\r}\NYou know, I told myself I'd be out of here
Dialogue: 0,1:56:20.64,1:56:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}顶多干到30多岁就会退出.{\r}\Nwhile I was still in my thirties.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:23.89,1:56:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}现在你看看我, 我真的是老了.{\r}\NAnd now look at me. I'm practically an old man.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:37.11,1:56:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}先生们.{\r}\NGentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.99,1:56:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}谢谢, 麦克.{\r}\NThanks, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:53.51,1:56:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}好...{\r}\NSo...
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.84,1:56:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}接下来我们干什么?{\r}\NWhat are we gonna do now?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:05.89,1:57:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}我们将让世界震撼.{\r}\NWe're gonna put a dent in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:18.32,1:57:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}致疯狂的人们,{\r}\NHere's to the crazy ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.70,1:57:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}特立独行者,{\r}\NThe misfits,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:24.12,1:57:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}叛逆的家伙们,{\r}\Nthe rebels,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.62,1:57:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}捣蛋鬼们,{\r}\Nthe troublemakers,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.83,1:57:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}方孔里的圆头钉子们(不适应社会的人),{\r}\Nthe round pegs in the square holes,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.42,1:57:35.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}那些想法与众不同的人们,{\r}\Nthe ones who see things differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:35.71,1:57:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们是那些痛恨条条框框的人,{\r}\NThey're not fond of rules,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:38.05,1:57:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们是对现状不满的人,{\r}\Nand they have no respect for the status quo.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:42.80,1:57:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你可能认同他们,{\r}\NYou can quote them,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:44.97,1:57:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}讨厌他们,{\r}\Ndisagree with them,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:46.85,1:57:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}赞美他们或者诋毁他们,{\r}\Nglorify or vilify them.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:49.94,1:57:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}你唯一无法做到的,{\r}\NAbout the only thing you can't do
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.23,1:57:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}就是对他们视而不见,{\r}\Nis ignore them.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.52,1:57:56.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为他们改变了世界,{\r}\NBecause they change things.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.90,1:57:59.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}他们推动了人类进步.{\r}\NThey push the human race forward.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:00.74,1:58:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}有些人可能认为他们是一群疯子,{\r}\NAnd while some may see them as the crazy ones,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:06.04,1:58:07.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}但我们认为他们是天才.{\r}\Nwe see genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:08.87,1:58:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}因为这群人足够疯狂{\r}\NBecause the people who are crazy enough
Dialogue: 0,1:58:11.33,1:58:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}勇于去想像他们能改变世界{\r}\Nto think they can change the world
Dialogue: 0,1:58:15.38,1:58:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}也正是他们改变着世界.{\r}\Nare the ones who do.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.18,1:58:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}录的如何?{\r}\NHow was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:59:39.30,1:59:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs26\1c&HFFFFFF&}2012年9月, Apple成为全球市值最高的公司.{\r}\NApple became the most valuable company in the market in September, 2012.

